78 // Set of virtual registers, based on BitVector. ----
79 struct RegisterSet { ----
80 RegisterSet() = default; 0
81 explicit RegisterSet(unsigned s, bool t = false) : Bits(s, t) {} ----
82 RegisterSet(const RegisterSet &RS) = default; 0
83 ----
84 void clear() { 0
85 Bits.clear(); 0
86 LRU.clear(); 0
87 } 0
88 ----
89 unsigned count() const { 0
90 return Bits.count(); 0
91 } ----
92 ----
93 unsigned find_first() const { 0
94 int First = Bits.find_first(); 0
95 if (First < 0) 0
96 return 0; 0
97 return x2v(First); 0
98 } ----
99 ----
100 unsigned find_next(unsigned Prev) const { 0
101 int Next = Bits.find_next(v2x(Prev)); 0
102 if (Next < 0) 0
103 return 0; 0
104 return x2v(Next); 0
105 } ----
106 ----
107 RegisterSet &insert(unsigned R) { 0
108 unsigned Idx = v2x(R); 0
109 ensure(Idx); 0
110 bool Exists = Bits.test(Idx); 0
111 Bits.set(Idx); 0
112 if (!Exists) { 0
113 LRU.push_back(Idx); 0
114 if (LRU.size() > RegisterSetLimit) { 0
115 unsigned T = LRU.front(); 0
116 Bits.reset(T); 0
117 LRU.pop_front(); 0
118 } ----
119 } ----
120 return *this; 0
121 } ----
122 RegisterSet &remove(unsigned R) { 0
123 unsigned Idx = v2x(R); 0
124 if (Idx < Bits.size()) { 0
125 bool Exists = Bits.test(Idx); 0
126 Bits.reset(Idx); 0
127 if (Exists) { 0
128 auto F = llvm::find(LRU, Idx); 0
129 assert(F != LRU.end()); 0
130 LRU.erase(F); 0
131 } ----
132 } ----
133 return *this; 0
134 } ----
135 ----
136 RegisterSet &insert(const RegisterSet &Rs) { 0
137 for (unsigned R = Rs.find_first(); R; R = Rs.find_next(R)) 0
138 insert(R); 0
139 return *this; 0
140 } ----
141 RegisterSet &remove(const RegisterSet &Rs) { 0
142 for (unsigned R = Rs.find_first(); R; R = Rs.find_next(R)) 0
143 remove(R); 0
144 return *this; 0
145 } ----
146 ----
147 bool operator[](unsigned R) const { 0
148 unsigned Idx = v2x(R); 0
149 return Idx < Bits.size() ? Bits[Idx] : false; 0
150 } ----
151 bool has(unsigned R) const { 0
152 unsigned Idx = v2x(R); 0
153 if (Idx >= Bits.size()) 0
154 return false; 0
155 return Bits.test(Idx); 0
156 } ----
157 ----
158 bool empty() const { ----
159 return !Bits.any(); ----
160 } ----
161 bool includes(const RegisterSet &Rs) const { ----
162 // A.test(B) <=> A-B != {} ----
163 return !Rs.Bits.test(Bits); ----
164 } ----
165 bool intersects(const RegisterSet &Rs) const { 0
166 return Bits.anyCommon(Rs.Bits); 0
167 } ----
168 ----
169 private: ----
170 BitVector Bits; ----
171 std::deque LRU; ----
172 ----
173 void ensure(unsigned Idx) { 0
174 if (Bits.size() <= Idx) 0
175 Bits.resize(std::max(Idx+1, 32U)); 0
176 } 0
177 ----
178 static inline unsigned v2x(unsigned v) { 0
179 return Register::virtReg2Index(v); 0
180 } ----
181 ----
182 static inline unsigned x2v(unsigned x) { 0
183 return Register::index2VirtReg(x); 0
184 } ----
185 }; ----

189 : RS(S), TRI(RI) {} ----

192 const PrintRegSet &P); ----
193 ----

197 }; ----
198 ----

200 LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED; ----

202 OS << '{'; 0
203 for (unsigned R = P.RS.find_first(); R; R = P.RS.find_next(R)) 0
204 OS << ' ' << printReg(R, P.TRI); 0
205 OS << " }"; 0
206 return OS; 0

269 // The purpose of this class is to provide a common facility to traverse ----
270 // the function top-down or bottom-up via the dominator tree, and keep ----
271 // track of the available registers. ----

273 public: ----
274 bool TopDown; ----
275 ----

292 bool HexagonBitSimplify::visitBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, Transformation &T, 0
293 RegisterSet &AVs) { ----
294 bool Changed = false; 0
295 ----
296 if (T.TopDown) 0
297 Changed = T.processBlock(B, AVs); 0
298 ----
299 RegisterSet Defs; 0
300 for (auto &I : B) 0
301 getInstrDefs(I, Defs); 0
302 RegisterSet NewAVs = AVs; 0
303 NewAVs.insert(Defs); 0
304 ----
305 for (auto *DTN : children(MDT->getNode(&B))) 0
306 Changed |= visitBlock(*(DTN->getBlock()), T, NewAVs); 0
307 ----
308 if (!T.TopDown) 0
309 Changed |= T.processBlock(B, AVs); 0
310 ----
311 return Changed; 0
312 } 0

317 void HexagonBitSimplify::getInstrDefs(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
318 RegisterSet &Defs) { ----

320 if (!Op.isReg() || !Op.isDef()) 0
321 continue; 0
322 Register R = Op.getReg(); 0
323 if (!R.isVirtual()) 0
324 continue; 0
325 Defs.insert(R); 0
326 } ----
327 } 0

341 // Check if all the bits in range [B, E) in both cells are equal. ----
342 bool HexagonBitSimplify::isEqual(const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC1, 0
343 uint16_t B1, const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC2, uint16_t B2, ----
344 uint16_t W) { ----
345 for (uint16_t i = 0; i < W; ++i) { 0
346 // If RC1[i] is "bottom", it cannot be proven equal to RC2[i]. ----
347 if (RC1[B1+i].Type == BitTracker::BitValue::Ref && RC1[B1+i].RefI.Reg == 0) 0
348 return false; 0
349 // Same for RC2[i]. ----
350 if (RC2[B2+i].Type == BitTracker::BitValue::Ref && RC2[B2+i].RefI.Reg == 0) 0
351 return false; 0
352 if (RC1[B1+i] != RC2[B2+i]) 0
353 return false; 0
354 } ----
355 return true; 0
356 } ----
357 ----
358 bool HexagonBitSimplify::isZero(const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC, 0
359 uint16_t B, uint16_t W) { ----
360 assert(B < RC.width() && B+W <= RC.width()); 0
361 for (uint16_t i = B; i < B+W; ++i) 0
362 if (!RC[i].is(0)) 0
363 return false; 0
364 return true; 0
365 } ----
366 ----
367 bool HexagonBitSimplify::getConst(const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC, 0
368 uint16_t B, uint16_t W, uint64_t &U) { ----
369 assert(B < RC.width() && B+W <= RC.width()); 0
370 int64_t T = 0; 0
371 for (uint16_t i = B+W; i > B; --i) { 0
372 const BitTracker::BitValue &BV = RC[i-1]; 0
373 T <<= 1; 0
374 if (BV.is(1)) 0
375 T |= 1; 0
376 else if (!BV.is(0)) 0
377 return false; 0
378 } ----
379 U = T; 0
380 return true; 0
381 } ----

383 bool HexagonBitSimplify::replaceReg(Register OldR, Register NewR, 0
384 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
385 if (!OldR.isVirtual() || !NewR.isVirtual()) 0
386 return false; 0
387 auto Begin = MRI.use_begin(OldR), End = MRI.use_end(); 0
388 decltype(End) NextI; 0
389 for (auto I = Begin; I != End; I = NextI) { 0
390 NextI = std::next(I); 0
391 I->setReg(NewR); 0
392 } ----
393 return Begin != End; 0
394 } ----
395 ----
396 bool HexagonBitSimplify::replaceRegWithSub(Register OldR, Register NewR, 0
397 unsigned NewSR, ----
398 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
399 if (!OldR.isVirtual() || !NewR.isVirtual()) 0
400 return false; 0
401 if (hasTiedUse(OldR, MRI, NewSR)) 0
402 return false; 0
403 auto Begin = MRI.use_begin(OldR), End = MRI.use_end(); 0
404 decltype(End) NextI; 0
405 for (auto I = Begin; I != End; I = NextI) { 0
406 NextI = std::next(I); 0
407 I->setReg(NewR); 0
408 I->setSubReg(NewSR); 0
409 } ----
410 return Begin != End; 0
411 } ----
412 ----
413 bool HexagonBitSimplify::replaceSubWithSub(Register OldR, unsigned OldSR, 0
414 Register NewR, unsigned NewSR, ----
415 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
416 if (!OldR.isVirtual() || !NewR.isVirtual()) 0
417 return false; 0
418 if (OldSR != NewSR && hasTiedUse(OldR, MRI, NewSR)) 0
419 return false; 0
420 auto Begin = MRI.use_begin(OldR), End = MRI.use_end(); 0
421 decltype(End) NextI; 0
422 for (auto I = Begin; I != End; I = NextI) { 0
423 NextI = std::next(I); 0
424 if (I->getSubReg() != OldSR) 0
425 continue; 0
426 I->setReg(NewR); 0
427 I->setSubReg(NewSR); 0
428 } ----
429 return Begin != End; 0
430 } ----

432 // For a register ref (pair Reg:Sub), set Begin to the position of the LSB ----
433 // of Sub in Reg, and set Width to the size of Sub in bits. Return true, ----
434 // if this succeeded, otherwise return false. ----
435 bool HexagonBitSimplify::getSubregMask(const BitTracker::RegisterRef &RR, 0
436 unsigned &Begin, unsigned &Width, MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
437 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI.getRegClass(RR.Reg); 0
438 if (RR.Sub == 0) { 0
439 Begin = 0; 0
440 Width = MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo()->getRegSizeInBits(*RC); 0
441 return true; 0
442 } ----
443 ----
444 Begin = 0; 0
445 ----
446 switch (RC->getID()) { 0
447 case Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClassID: 0
448 case Hexagon::HvxWRRegClassID: ----
449 Width = MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo()->getRegSizeInBits(*RC) / 2; 0
450 if (RR.Sub == Hexagon::isub_hi || RR.Sub == Hexagon::vsub_hi) 0
451 Begin = Width; 0
452 break; 0
453 default: 0
454 return false; 0
455 } ----
456 return true; 0
457 } ----

460 // For a REG_SEQUENCE, set SL to the low subregister and SH to the high ----
461 // subregister. ----
462 bool HexagonBitSimplify::parseRegSequence(const MachineInstr &I, 0
463 BitTracker::RegisterRef &SL, BitTracker::RegisterRef &SH, ----
464 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
465 assert(I.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE); 0
466 unsigned Sub1 = I.getOperand(2).getImm(), Sub2 = I.getOperand(4).getImm(); 0
467 auto &DstRC = *MRI.getRegClass(I.getOperand(0).getReg()); 0
468 auto &HRI = static_cast( ----
469 *MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo()); 0
470 unsigned SubLo = HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(DstRC, Hexagon::ps_sub_lo); 0
471 unsigned SubHi = HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(DstRC, Hexagon::ps_sub_hi); 0
472 assert((Sub1 == SubLo && Sub2 == SubHi) || (Sub1 == SubHi && Sub2 == SubLo)); 0
473 if (Sub1 == SubLo && Sub2 == SubHi) { 0
474 SL = I.getOperand(1); 0
475 SH = I.getOperand(3); 0
476 return true; 0
477 } ----
478 if (Sub1 == SubHi && Sub2 == SubLo) { 0
479 SH = I.getOperand(1); 0
480 SL = I.getOperand(3); 0
481 return true; 0
482 } ----
483 return false; 0
484 } ----

486 // All stores (except 64-bit stores) take a 32-bit register as the source ----
487 // of the value to be stored. If the instruction stores into a location ----
488 // that is shorter than 32 bits, some bits of the source register are not ----
489 // used. For each store instruction, calculate the set of used bits in ----
490 // the source register, and set appropriate bits in Bits. Return true if ----
491 // the bits are calculated, false otherwise. ----
492 bool HexagonBitSimplify::getUsedBitsInStore(unsigned Opc, BitVector &Bits, 0
493 uint16_t Begin) { ----
494 using namespace Hexagon; ----
495 ----
496 switch (Opc) { 0
497 // Store byte ----
498 case S2_storerb_io: // memb(Rs32+#s11:0)=Rt32 0
499 case S2_storerbnew_io: // memb(Rs32+#s11:0)=Nt8.new ----
500 case S2_pstorerbt_io: // if (Pv4) memb(Rs32+#u6:0)=Rt32 ----
501 case S2_pstorerbf_io: // if (!Pv4) memb(Rs32+#u6:0)=Rt32 ----
502 case S4_pstorerbtnew_io: // if (Pv4.new) memb(Rs32+#u6:0)=Rt32 ----
503 case S4_pstorerbfnew_io: // if (!Pv4.new) memb(Rs32+#u6:0)=Rt32 ----
504 case S2_pstorerbnewt_io: // if (Pv4) memb(Rs32+#u6:0)=Nt8.new ----
505 case S2_pstorerbnewf_io: // if (!Pv4) memb(Rs32+#u6:0)=Nt8.new ----
506 case S4_pstorerbnewtnew_io: // if (Pv4.new) memb(Rs32+#u6:0)=Nt8.new ----
507 case S4_pstorerbnewfnew_io: // if (!Pv4.new) memb(Rs32+#u6:0)=Nt8.new ----
508 case S2_storerb_pi: // memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Rt32 ----
509 case S2_storerbnew_pi: // memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Nt8.new ----
510 case S2_pstorerbt_pi: // if (Pv4) memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Rt32 ----
511 case S2_pstorerbf_pi: // if (!Pv4) memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Rt32 ----
512 case S2_pstorerbtnew_pi: // if (Pv4.new) memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Rt32 ----
513 case S2_pstorerbfnew_pi: // if (!Pv4.new) memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Rt32 ----
514 case S2_pstorerbnewt_pi: // if (Pv4) memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Nt8.new ----
515 case S2_pstorerbnewf_pi: // if (!Pv4) memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Nt8.new ----
516 case S2_pstorerbnewtnew_pi: // if (Pv4.new) memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Nt8.new ----
517 case S2_pstorerbnewfnew_pi: // if (!Pv4.new) memb(Rx32++#s4:0)=Nt8.new ----
518 case S4_storerb_ap: // memb(Re32=#U6)=Rt32 ----
519 case S4_storerbnew_ap: // memb(Re32=#U6)=Nt8.new ----
520 case S2_storerb_pr: // memb(Rx32++Mu2)=Rt32 ----
521 case S2_storerbnew_pr: // memb(Rx32++Mu2)=Nt8.new ----
522 case S4_storerb_ur: // memb(Ru32<<#u2+#U6)=Rt32 ----
523 case S4_storerbnew_ur: // memb(Ru32<<#u2+#U6)=Nt8.new ----
524 case S2_storerb_pbr: // memb(Rx32++Mu2:brev)=Rt32 ----
525 case S2_storerbnew_pbr: // memb(Rx32++Mu2:brev)=Nt8.new ----
526 case S2_storerb_pci: // memb(Rx32++#s4:0:circ(Mu2))=Rt32 ----
527 case S2_storerbnew_pci: // memb(Rx32++#s4:0:circ(Mu2))=Nt8.new ----
528 case S2_storerb_pcr: // memb(Rx32++I:circ(Mu2))=Rt32 ----
529 case S2_storerbnew_pcr: // memb(Rx32++I:circ(Mu2))=Nt8.new ----
530 case S4_storerb_rr: // memb(Rs32+Ru32<<#u2)=Rt32 ----
531 case S4_storerbnew_rr: // memb(Rs32+Ru32<<#u2)=Nt8.new ----
532 case S4_pstorerbt_rr: // if (Pv4) memb(Rs32+Ru32<<#u2)=Rt32 ----
533 case S4_pstorerbf_rr: // if (!Pv4) memb(Rs32+Ru32<<#u2)=Rt32 ----
534 case S4_pstorerbtnew_rr: // if (Pv4.new) memb(Rs32+Ru32<<#u2)=Rt32 ----
535 case S4_pstorerbfnew_rr: // if (!Pv4.new) memb(Rs32+Ru32<<#u2)=Rt32 ----

539 case S4_pstorerbnewfnew_rr: // if (!Pv4.new) memb(Rs32+Ru32<<#u2)=Nt8.new ----
540 case S2_storerbgp: // memb(gp+#u16:0)=Rt32 ----
541 case S2_storerbnewgp: // memb(gp+#u16:0)=Nt8.new ----
542 case S4_pstorerbt_abs: // if (Pv4) memb(#u6)=Rt32 ----
543 case S4_pstorerbf_abs: // if (!Pv4) memb(#u6)=Rt32 ----

546 case S4_pstorerbnewt_abs: // if (Pv4) memb(#u6)=Nt8.new ----
547 case S4_pstorerbnewf_abs: // if (!Pv4) memb(#u6)=Nt8.new ----
548 case S4_pstorerbnewtnew_abs: // if (Pv4.new) memb(#u6)=Nt8.new ----
549 case S4_pstorerbnewfnew_abs: // if (!Pv4.new) memb(#u6)=Nt8.new ----
550 Bits.set(Begin, Begin+8); 0
551 return true; 0
552 ----
553 // Store low half ----
554 case S2_storerh_io: // memh(Rs32+#s11:1)=Rt32 0

643 // For an instruction with opcode Opc, calculate the set of bits that it ----
644 // uses in a register in operand OpN. This only calculates the set of used ----
645 // bits for cases where it does not depend on any operands (as is the case ----
646 // in shifts, for example). For concrete instructions from a program, the ----
647 // operand may be a subregister of a larger register, while Bits would ----
648 // correspond to the larger register in its entirety. Because of that, ----
649 // the parameter Begin can be used to indicate which bit of Bits should be ----
650 // considered the LSB of the operand. ----
651 bool HexagonBitSimplify::getUsedBits(unsigned Opc, unsigned OpN, 0
652 BitVector &Bits, uint16_t Begin, const HexagonInstrInfo &HII) { ----
653 using namespace Hexagon; ----

655 const MCInstrDesc &D = HII.get(Opc); 0
656 if (D.mayStore()) { 0

658 return getUsedBitsInStore(Opc, Bits, Begin); 0
659 return false; 0

673 break; 0

675 // One register source. Used bits: R1[0-15]. ----

921 ----
922 // Calculate the register class that matches Reg:Sub. For example, if ----
923 // %1 is a double register, then %1:isub_hi would match the "int" ----
924 // register class. ----
925 const TargetRegisterClass *HexagonBitSimplify::getFinalVRegClass( 0
926 const BitTracker::RegisterRef &RR, MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
927 if (!RR.Reg.isVirtual()) 0
928 return nullptr; 0
929 auto *RC = MRI.getRegClass(RR.Reg); 0
930 if (RR.Sub == 0) 0
931 return RC; 0
932 auto &HRI = static_cast( ----
933 *MRI.getTargetRegisterInfo()); 0
934 ----
935 auto VerifySR = [&HRI] (const TargetRegisterClass *RC, unsigned Sub) -> void { 0
936 (void)HRI; ----
937 assert(Sub == HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(*RC, Hexagon::ps_sub_lo) || 0
938 Sub == HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(*RC, Hexagon::ps_sub_hi)); ----
939 }; 0
940 ----
941 switch (RC->getID()) { 0
942 case Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClassID: 0
943 VerifySR(RC, RR.Sub); 0
944 return &Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass; 0
945 case Hexagon::HvxWRRegClassID: 0
946 VerifySR(RC, RR.Sub); 0
947 return &Hexagon::HvxVRRegClass; 0
948 } ----
949 return nullptr; 0
950 } ----
951 ----
952 // Check if RD could be replaced with RS at any possible use of RD. ----
953 // For example a predicate register cannot be replaced with a integer ----
954 // register, but a 64-bit register with a subregister can be replaced ----
955 // with a 32-bit register. ----
956 bool HexagonBitSimplify::isTransparentCopy(const BitTracker::RegisterRef &RD, 0
957 const BitTracker::RegisterRef &RS, MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { ----
958 if (!RD.Reg.isVirtual() || !RS.Reg.isVirtual()) 0
959 return false; 0
960 // Return false if one (or both) classes are nullptr. ----
961 auto *DRC = getFinalVRegClass(RD, MRI); 0
962 if (!DRC) 0
963 return false; 0
964 ----
965 return DRC == getFinalVRegClass(RS, MRI); 0
966 } ----
967 ----
968 bool HexagonBitSimplify::hasTiedUse(unsigned Reg, MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, 0
969 unsigned NewSub) { ----
970 if (!PreserveTiedOps) 0
971 return false; 0
972 return llvm::any_of(MRI.use_operands(Reg), 0
973 [NewSub] (const MachineOperand &Op) -> bool { 0
974 return Op.getSubReg() != NewSub && Op.isTied(); 0
975 }); 0
976 } ----

978 namespace { ----

980 class DeadCodeElimination { ----
981 public: ----
982 DeadCodeElimination(MachineFunction &mf, MachineDominatorTree &mdt) 0
983 : MF(mf), HII(*MF.getSubtarget().getInstrInfo()), 0
984 MDT(mdt), MRI(mf.getRegInfo()) {} 0
985 ----
986 bool run() { 0
987 return runOnNode(MDT.getRootNode()); 0
988 } ----
989 ----
990 private: ----
991 bool isDead(unsigned R) const; ----
992 bool runOnNode(MachineDomTreeNode *N); ----
993 ----
994 MachineFunction &MF; ----
995 const HexagonInstrInfo &HII; ----
996 MachineDominatorTree &MDT; ----
997 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI; ----
998 }; ----
999 ----
1000 } // end anonymous namespace ----
1001 ----
1002 bool DeadCodeElimination::isDead(unsigned R) const { 0
1003 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MRI.use_operands(R)) { 0
1004 const MachineInstr *UseI = MO.getParent(); 0
1005 if (UseI->isDebugValue()) 0
1006 continue; 0
1007 if (UseI->isPHI()) { 0
1008 assert(!UseI->getOperand(0).getSubReg()); 0
1009 Register DR = UseI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1010 if (DR == R) 0
1011 continue; 0
1012 } ----
1013 return false; 0
1014 } ----
1015 return true; 0
1016 } ----
1017 ----
1018 bool DeadCodeElimination::runOnNode(MachineDomTreeNode *N) { 0
1019 bool Changed = false; 0
1020 ----
1021 for (auto *DTN : children(N)) 0
1022 Changed |= runOnNode(DTN); 0
1023 ----
1024 MachineBasicBlock *B = N->getBlock(); 0
1025 std::vector Instrs; 0
1026 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::reverse(*B)) 0
1027 Instrs.push_back(&MI); 0
1028 ----
1029 for (auto *MI : Instrs) { 0
1030 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1031 // Do not touch lifetime markers. This is why the target-independent DCE ----
1032 // cannot be used. ----
1033 if (Opc == TargetOpcode::LIFETIME_START || 0
1034 Opc == TargetOpcode::LIFETIME_END) ----
1035 continue; 0
1036 bool Store = false; 0
1037 if (MI->isInlineAsm()) 0
1038 continue; 0
1039 // Delete PHIs if possible. ----
1040 if (!MI->isPHI() && !MI->isSafeToMove(nullptr, Store)) 0
1041 continue; 0
1042 ----
1043 bool AllDead = true; 0
1044 SmallVector Regs; 0
1045 for (auto &Op : MI->operands()) { 0
1046 if (!Op.isReg() || !Op.isDef()) 0
1047 continue; 0
1048 Register R = Op.getReg(); 0
1049 if (!R.isVirtual() || !isDead(R)) { 0
1050 AllDead = false; 0
1051 break; 0
1052 } ----
1053 Regs.push_back(R); 0
1054 } ----
1055 if (!AllDead) 0
1056 continue; 0
1057 ----
1058 B->erase(MI); 0
1059 for (unsigned i = 0, n = Regs.size(); i != n; ++i) 0
1060 MRI.markUsesInDebugValueAsUndef(Regs[i]); 0
1061 Changed = true; 0
1062 } 0
1063 ----
1064 return Changed; 0
1065 } 0
1066 ----
1067 namespace { ----
1068 ----
1069 // Eliminate redundant instructions ----
1070 // ----
1071 // This transformation will identify instructions where the output register ----
1072 // is the same as one of its input registers. This only works on instructions ----
1073 // that define a single register (unlike post-increment loads, for example). ----
1074 // The equality check is actually more detailed: the code calculates which ----
1075 // bits of the output are used, and only compares these bits with the input ----
1076 // registers. ----
1077 // If the output matches an input, the instruction is replaced with COPY. ----
1078 // The copies will be removed by another transformation. ----
1079 class RedundantInstrElimination : public Transformation { ----
1080 public: ----
1081 RedundantInstrElimination(BitTracker &bt, const HexagonInstrInfo &hii, 0
1082 const HexagonRegisterInfo &hri, MachineRegisterInfo &mri) ----
1083 : Transformation(true), HII(hii), HRI(hri), MRI(mri), BT(bt) {} 0
1084 ----
1085 bool processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, const RegisterSet &AVs) override; ----
1086 ----
1087 private: ----
1088 bool isLossyShiftLeft(const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpN, ----
1089 unsigned &LostB, unsigned &LostE); ----
1090 bool isLossyShiftRight(const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpN, ----
1091 unsigned &LostB, unsigned &LostE); ----
1092 bool computeUsedBits(unsigned Reg, BitVector &Bits); ----
1093 bool computeUsedBits(const MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpN, BitVector &Bits, ----
1094 uint16_t Begin); ----
1095 bool usedBitsEqual(BitTracker::RegisterRef RD, BitTracker::RegisterRef RS); ----
1096 ----
1097 const HexagonInstrInfo &HII; ----
1098 const HexagonRegisterInfo &HRI; ----
1099 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI; ----
1100 BitTracker &BT; ----
1101 }; ----
1102 ----
1103 } // end anonymous namespace ----
1104 ----
1105 // Check if the instruction is a lossy shift left, where the input being ----
1106 // shifted is the operand OpN of MI. If true, [LostB, LostE) is the range ----
1107 // of bit indices that are lost. ----
1108 bool RedundantInstrElimination::isLossyShiftLeft(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
1109 unsigned OpN, unsigned &LostB, unsigned &LostE) { ----
1110 using namespace Hexagon; ----
1111 ----
1112 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1113 unsigned ImN, RegN, Width; ----
1114 switch (Opc) { 0
1115 case S2_asl_i_p: 0
1116 ImN = 2; 0
1117 RegN = 1; 0
1118 Width = 64; 0
1119 break; 0
1120 case S2_asl_i_p_acc: 0
1121 case S2_asl_i_p_and: ----
1122 case S2_asl_i_p_nac: ----
1123 case S2_asl_i_p_or: ----
1124 case S2_asl_i_p_xacc: ----
1125 ImN = 3; 0
1126 RegN = 2; 0
1127 Width = 64; 0
1128 break; 0
1129 case S2_asl_i_r: 0
1130 ImN = 2; 0
1131 RegN = 1; 0
1132 Width = 32; 0
1133 break; 0
1134 case S2_addasl_rrri: 0
1135 case S4_andi_asl_ri: ----
1136 case S4_ori_asl_ri: ----
1137 case S4_addi_asl_ri: ----
1138 case S4_subi_asl_ri: ----
1139 case S2_asl_i_r_acc: ----
1140 case S2_asl_i_r_and: ----
1141 case S2_asl_i_r_nac: ----
1142 case S2_asl_i_r_or: ----
1143 case S2_asl_i_r_sat: ----
1144 case S2_asl_i_r_xacc: ----
1145 ImN = 3; 0
1146 RegN = 2; 0
1147 Width = 32; 0
1148 break; 0
1149 default: 0
1150 return false; 0
1151 } ----
1152 ----
1153 if (RegN != OpN) 0
1154 return false; 0
1155 ----
1156 assert(MI.getOperand(ImN).isImm()); 0
1157 unsigned S = MI.getOperand(ImN).getImm(); 0
1158 if (S == 0) 0
1159 return false; 0
1160 LostB = Width-S; 0
1161 LostE = Width; 0
1162 return true; 0
1163 } ----
1164 ----
1165 // Check if the instruction is a lossy shift right, where the input being ----
1166 // shifted is the operand OpN of MI. If true, [LostB, LostE) is the range ----
1167 // of bit indices that are lost. ----
1168 bool RedundantInstrElimination::isLossyShiftRight(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
1169 unsigned OpN, unsigned &LostB, unsigned &LostE) { ----
1170 using namespace Hexagon; ----
1171 ----
1172 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1173 unsigned ImN, RegN; ----
1174 switch (Opc) { 0
1175 case S2_asr_i_p: 0
1176 case S2_lsr_i_p: ----
1177 ImN = 2; 0
1178 RegN = 1; 0
1179 break; 0
1180 case S2_asr_i_p_acc: 0
1181 case S2_asr_i_p_and: ----
1182 case S2_asr_i_p_nac: ----
1183 case S2_asr_i_p_or: ----
1184 case S2_lsr_i_p_acc: ----
1185 case S2_lsr_i_p_and: ----
1186 case S2_lsr_i_p_nac: ----
1187 case S2_lsr_i_p_or: ----
1188 case S2_lsr_i_p_xacc: ----
1189 ImN = 3; 0
1190 RegN = 2; 0
1191 break; 0
1192 case S2_asr_i_r: 0
1193 case S2_lsr_i_r: ----
1194 ImN = 2; 0
1195 RegN = 1; 0
1196 break; 0
1197 case S4_andi_lsr_ri: 0
1198 case S4_ori_lsr_ri: ----
1199 case S4_addi_lsr_ri: ----
1200 case S4_subi_lsr_ri: ----
1201 case S2_asr_i_r_acc: ----
1202 case S2_asr_i_r_and: ----
1203 case S2_asr_i_r_nac: ----
1204 case S2_asr_i_r_or: ----
1205 case S2_lsr_i_r_acc: ----
1206 case S2_lsr_i_r_and: ----
1207 case S2_lsr_i_r_nac: ----
1208 case S2_lsr_i_r_or: ----
1209 case S2_lsr_i_r_xacc: ----
1210 ImN = 3; 0
1211 RegN = 2; 0
1212 break; 0
1213 ----
1214 default: 0
1215 return false; 0
1216 } ----
1217 ----
1218 if (RegN != OpN) 0
1219 return false; 0
1220 ----
1221 assert(MI.getOperand(ImN).isImm()); 0
1222 unsigned S = MI.getOperand(ImN).getImm(); 0
1223 LostB = 0; 0
1224 LostE = S; 0
1225 return true; 0
1226 } ----
1227 ----
1228 // Calculate the bit vector that corresponds to the used bits of register Reg. ----
1229 // The vector Bits has the same size, as the size of Reg in bits. If the cal- ----
1230 // culation fails (i.e. the used bits are unknown), it returns false. Other- ----
1231 // wise, it returns true and sets the corresponding bits in Bits. ----
1232 bool RedundantInstrElimination::computeUsedBits(unsigned Reg, BitVector &Bits) { 0
1233 BitVector Used(Bits.size()); 0
1234 RegisterSet Visited; 0
1235 std::vector Pending; 0
1236 Pending.push_back(Reg); 0
1237 ----
1238 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Pending.size(); ++i) { 0
1239 unsigned R = Pending[i]; 0
1240 if (Visited.has(R)) 0
1241 continue; 0
1242 Visited.insert(R); 0
1243 for (auto I = MRI.use_begin(R), E = MRI.use_end(); I != E; ++I) { 0
1244 BitTracker::RegisterRef UR = *I; 0
1245 unsigned B, W; ----
1246 if (!HBS::getSubregMask(UR, B, W, MRI)) 0
1247 return false; 0
1248 MachineInstr &UseI = *I->getParent(); 0
1249 if (UseI.isPHI() || UseI.isCopy()) { 0
1250 Register DefR = UseI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1251 if (!DefR.isVirtual()) 0
1252 return false; 0
1253 Pending.push_back(DefR); 0
1254 } else { ----
1255 if (!computeUsedBits(UseI, I.getOperandNo(), Used, B)) 0
1256 return false; 0
1257 } ----
1258 } ----
1259 } ----
1260 Bits |= Used; 0
1261 return true; 0
1262 } 0
1263 ----
1264 // Calculate the bits used by instruction MI in a register in operand OpN. ----
1265 // Return true/false if the calculation succeeds/fails. If is succeeds, set ----
1266 // used bits in Bits. This function does not reset any bits in Bits, so ----
1267 // subsequent calls over different instructions will result in the union ----
1268 // of the used bits in all these instructions. ----
1269 // The register in question may be used with a sub-register, whereas Bits ----
1270 // holds the bits for the entire register. To keep track of that, the ----
1271 // argument Begin indicates where in Bits is the lowest-significant bit ----
1272 // of the register used in operand OpN. For example, in instruction: ----
1273 // %1 = S2_lsr_i_r %2:isub_hi, 10 ----
1274 // the operand 1 is a 32-bit register, which happens to be a subregister ----
1275 // of the 64-bit register %2, and that subregister starts at position 32. ----
1276 // In this case Begin=32, since Bits[32] would be the lowest-significant bit ----
1277 // of %2:isub_hi. ----
1278 bool RedundantInstrElimination::computeUsedBits(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
1279 unsigned OpN, BitVector &Bits, uint16_t Begin) { ----
1280 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1281 BitVector T(Bits.size()); 0
1282 bool GotBits = HBS::getUsedBits(Opc, OpN, T, Begin, HII); 0
1283 // Even if we don't have bits yet, we could still provide some information ----
1284 // if the instruction is a lossy shift: the lost bits will be marked as ----
1285 // not used. ----
1286 unsigned LB, LE; ----
1287 if (isLossyShiftLeft(MI, OpN, LB, LE) || isLossyShiftRight(MI, OpN, LB, LE)) { 0
1288 assert(MI.getOperand(OpN).isReg()); 0
1289 BitTracker::RegisterRef RR = MI.getOperand(OpN); 0
1290 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = HBS::getFinalVRegClass(RR, MRI); 0
1291 uint16_t Width = HRI.getRegSizeInBits(*RC); 0
1292 ----
1293 if (!GotBits) 0
1294 T.set(Begin, Begin+Width); 0
1295 assert(LB <= LE && LB < Width && LE <= Width); 0
1296 T.reset(Begin+LB, Begin+LE); 0
1297 GotBits = true; 0
1298 } ----
1299 if (GotBits) 0
1300 Bits |= T; 0
1301 return GotBits; 0
1302 } 0
1303 ----
1304 // Calculates the used bits in RD ("defined register"), and checks if these ----
1305 // bits in RS ("used register") and RD are identical. ----
1306 bool RedundantInstrElimination::usedBitsEqual(BitTracker::RegisterRef RD, 0
1307 BitTracker::RegisterRef RS) { ----
1308 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &DC = BT.lookup(RD.Reg); 0
1309 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &SC = BT.lookup(RS.Reg); 0
1310 ----
1311 unsigned DB, DW; ----
1312 if (!HBS::getSubregMask(RD, DB, DW, MRI)) 0
1313 return false; 0
1314 unsigned SB, SW; ----
1315 if (!HBS::getSubregMask(RS, SB, SW, MRI)) 0
1316 return false; 0
1317 if (SW != DW) 0
1318 return false; 0
1319 ----
1320 BitVector Used(DC.width()); 0
1321 if (!computeUsedBits(RD.Reg, Used)) 0
1322 return false; 0
1323 ----
1324 for (unsigned i = 0; i != DW; ++i) 0
1325 if (Used[i+DB] && DC[DB+i] != SC[SB+i]) 0
1326 return false; 0
1327 return true; 0
1328 } 0
1329 ----
1330 bool RedundantInstrElimination::processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, 0
1331 const RegisterSet&) { ----
1332 if (!BT.reached(&B)) 0
1333 return false; 0
1334 bool Changed = false; 0
1335 ----
1336 for (auto I = B.begin(), E = B.end(); I != E; ++I) { 0
1337 MachineInstr *MI = &*I; 0
1338 ----
1339 if (MI->getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::COPY) 0
1340 continue; 0
1341 if (MI->isPHI() || MI->hasUnmodeledSideEffects() || MI->isInlineAsm()) 0
1342 continue; 0
1343 unsigned NumD = MI->getDesc().getNumDefs(); 0
1344 if (NumD != 1) 0
1345 continue; 0
1346 ----
1347 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD = MI->getOperand(0); 0
1348 if (!BT.has(RD.Reg)) 0
1349 continue; 0
1350 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &DC = BT.lookup(RD.Reg); 0
1351 auto At = MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI); 0
1352 ----
1353 // Find a source operand that is equal to the result. ----
1354 for (auto &Op : MI->uses()) { 0
1355 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
1356 continue; 0
1357 BitTracker::RegisterRef RS = Op; 0
1358 if (!BT.has(RS.Reg)) 0
1359 continue; 0
1360 if (!HBS::isTransparentCopy(RD, RS, MRI)) 0
1361 continue; 0
1362 ----
1363 unsigned BN, BW; ----
1364 if (!HBS::getSubregMask(RS, BN, BW, MRI)) 0
1365 continue; 0
1366 ----
1367 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &SC = BT.lookup(RS.Reg); 0
1368 if (!usedBitsEqual(RD, RS) && !HBS::isEqual(DC, 0, SC, BN, BW)) 0
1369 continue; 0
1370 ----
1371 // If found, replace the instruction with a COPY. ----
1372 const DebugLoc &DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
1373 const TargetRegisterClass *FRC = HBS::getFinalVRegClass(RD, MRI); 0
1374 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(FRC); 0
1375 MachineInstr *CopyI = ----
1376 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(TargetOpcode::COPY), NewR) 0
1377 .addReg(RS.Reg, 0, RS.Sub); 0
1378 HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, RD.Sub, NewR, 0, MRI); 0
1379 // This pass can create copies between registers that don't have the ----
1380 // exact same values. Updating the tracker has to involve updating ----
1381 // all dependent cells. Example: ----
1382 // %1 = inst %2 ; %1 != %2, but used bits are equal ----
1383 // ----
1384 // %3 = copy %2 ; <- inserted ----
1385 // ... = %3 ; <- replaced from %2 ----
1386 // Indirectly, we can create a "copy" between %1 and %2 even ----
1387 // though their exact values do not match. ----
1388 BT.visit(*CopyI); 0
1389 Changed = true; 0
1390 break; 0
1391 } ----
1392 } ----
1393 ----
1394 return Changed; 0
1395 } ----
1396 ----

1399 // Recognize instructions that produce constant values known at compile-time. ----
1400 // Replace them with register definitions that load these constants directly. ----
1401 class ConstGeneration : public Transformation { ----
1402 public: ----
1403 ConstGeneration(BitTracker &bt, const HexagonInstrInfo &hii, 0
1404 MachineRegisterInfo &mri) ----
1405 : Transformation(true), HII(hii), MRI(mri), BT(bt) {} 0
1406 ----
1407 bool processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, const RegisterSet &AVs) override; ----
1408 static bool isTfrConst(const MachineInstr &MI); ----
1409 ----
1410 private: ----
1411 Register genTfrConst(const TargetRegisterClass *RC, int64_t C, ----
1412 MachineBasicBlock &B, MachineBasicBlock::iterator At, ----
1413 DebugLoc &DL); ----
1414 ----
1415 const HexagonInstrInfo &HII; ----
1416 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI; ----
1417 BitTracker &BT; ----
1418 }; ----
1419 ----
1420 } // end anonymous namespace ----
1421 ----
1422 bool ConstGeneration::isTfrConst(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1423 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1424 switch (Opc) { 0
1425 case Hexagon::A2_combineii: 0
1426 case Hexagon::A4_combineii: ----
1427 case Hexagon::A2_tfrsi: ----
1428 case Hexagon::A2_tfrpi: ----
1429 case Hexagon::PS_true: ----
1430 case Hexagon::PS_false: ----
1431 case Hexagon::CONST32: ----
1432 case Hexagon::CONST64: ----
1433 return true; 0
1434 } ----
1435 return false; 0
1436 } ----
1437 ----
1438 // Generate a transfer-immediate instruction that is appropriate for the ----
1439 // register class and the actual value being transferred. ----
1440 Register ConstGeneration::genTfrConst(const TargetRegisterClass *RC, int64_t C, 0
1441 MachineBasicBlock &B, ----
1442 MachineBasicBlock::iterator At, ----
1443 DebugLoc &DL) { ----
1444 Register Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1445 if (RC == &Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass) { 0
1446 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::A2_tfrsi), Reg) 0
1447 .addImm(int32_t(C)); 0
1448 return Reg; 0
1449 } ----
1450 ----
1451 if (RC == &Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass) { 0
1452 if (isInt<8>(C)) { 0
1453 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::A2_tfrpi), Reg) 0
1454 .addImm(C); 0
1455 return Reg; 0
1456 } ----
1457 ----
1458 unsigned Lo = Lo_32(C), Hi = Hi_32(C); 0
1459 if (isInt<8>(Lo) || isInt<8>(Hi)) { 0
1460 unsigned Opc = isInt<8>(Lo) ? Hexagon::A2_combineii 0
1461 : Hexagon::A4_combineii; 0
1462 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Opc), Reg) 0
1463 .addImm(int32_t(Hi)) 0
1464 .addImm(int32_t(Lo)); 0
1465 return Reg; 0
1466 } ----
1467 MachineFunction *MF = B.getParent(); 0
1468 auto &HST = MF->getSubtarget(); 0
1469 ----
1470 // Disable CONST64 for tiny core since it takes a LD resource. ----
1471 if (!HST.isTinyCore() || 0
1472 MF->getFunction().hasOptSize()) { 0
1473 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::CONST64), Reg) 0
1474 .addImm(C); 0
1475 return Reg; 0
1476 } ----
1477 } ----
1478 ----
1479 if (RC == &Hexagon::PredRegsRegClass) { 0
1480 unsigned Opc; ----
1481 if (C == 0) 0
1482 Opc = Hexagon::PS_false; 0
1483 else if ((C & 0xFF) == 0xFF) 0
1484 Opc = Hexagon::PS_true; 0
1485 else ----
1486 return 0; 0
1487 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Opc), Reg); 0
1488 return Reg; 0
1489 } ----
1490 ----
1491 return 0; 0
1492 } ----
1493 ----
1494 bool ConstGeneration::processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, const RegisterSet&) { 0
1495 if (!BT.reached(&B)) 0
1496 return false; 0
1497 bool Changed = false; 0
1498 RegisterSet Defs; 0
1499 ----
1500 for (auto I = B.begin(), E = B.end(); I != E; ++I) { 0
1501 if (isTfrConst(*I)) 0
1502 continue; 0
1503 Defs.clear(); 0
1504 HBS::getInstrDefs(*I, Defs); 0
1505 if (Defs.count() != 1) 0
1506 continue; 0
1507 Register DR = Defs.find_first(); 0
1508 if (!DR.isVirtual()) 0
1509 continue; 0
1510 uint64_t U; ----
1511 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &DRC = BT.lookup(DR); 0
1512 if (HBS::getConst(DRC, 0, DRC.width(), U)) { 0
1513 int64_t C = U; 0
1514 DebugLoc DL = I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1515 auto At = I->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() : I; 0
1516 Register ImmReg = genTfrConst(MRI.getRegClass(DR), C, B, At, DL); 0
1517 if (ImmReg) { 0
1518 HBS::replaceReg(DR, ImmReg, MRI); 0
1519 BT.put(ImmReg, DRC); 0
1520 Changed = true; 0
1521 } ----
1522 } 0
1523 } ----
1524 return Changed; 0
1525 } 0

1529 // Identify pairs of available registers which hold identical values. ----
1530 // In such cases, only one of them needs to be calculated, the other one ----
1531 // will be defined as a copy of the first. ----
1532 class CopyGeneration : public Transformation { ----

1534 CopyGeneration(BitTracker &bt, const HexagonInstrInfo &hii, 0

1536 : Transformation(true), HII(hii), HRI(hri), MRI(mri), BT(bt) {} 0
1537 ----
1538 bool processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, const RegisterSet &AVs) override; ----
1539 ----
1540 private: ----
1541 bool findMatch(const BitTracker::RegisterRef &Inp, ----
1542 BitTracker::RegisterRef &Out, const RegisterSet &AVs); ----
1543 ----
1544 const HexagonInstrInfo &HII; ----
1545 const HexagonRegisterInfo &HRI; ----
1546 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI; ----
1547 BitTracker &BT; ----
1548 RegisterSet Forbidden; ----
1549 }; ----
1550 ----
1551 // Eliminate register copies RD = RS, by replacing the uses of RD with ----
1552 // with uses of RS. ----
1553 class CopyPropagation : public Transformation { ----
1554 public: ----
1555 CopyPropagation(const HexagonRegisterInfo &hri, MachineRegisterInfo &mri) 0
1556 : Transformation(false), HRI(hri), MRI(mri) {} 0
1557 ----
1558 bool processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, const RegisterSet &AVs) override; ----
1559 ----
1560 static bool isCopyReg(unsigned Opc, bool NoConv); ----
1561 ----
1562 private: ----
1563 bool propagateRegCopy(MachineInstr &MI); ----
1564 ----
1565 const HexagonRegisterInfo &HRI; ----
1566 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI; ----
1567 }; ----
1568 ----
1569 } // end anonymous namespace ----
1570 ----
1571 /// Check if there is a register in AVs that is identical to Inp. If so, ----
1572 /// set Out to the found register. The output may be a pair Reg:Sub. ----
1573 bool CopyGeneration::findMatch(const BitTracker::RegisterRef &Inp, 0
1574 BitTracker::RegisterRef &Out, const RegisterSet &AVs) { ----
1575 if (!BT.has(Inp.Reg)) 0
1576 return false; 0
1577 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &InpRC = BT.lookup(Inp.Reg); 0
1578 auto *FRC = HBS::getFinalVRegClass(Inp, MRI); 0
1579 unsigned B, W; ----
1580 if (!HBS::getSubregMask(Inp, B, W, MRI)) 0
1581 return false; 0
1582 ----
1583 for (Register R = AVs.find_first(); R; R = AVs.find_next(R)) { 0
1584 if (!BT.has(R) || Forbidden[R]) 0
1585 continue; 0
1586 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC = BT.lookup(R); 0
1587 unsigned RW = RC.width(); 0
1588 if (W == RW) { 0
1589 if (FRC != MRI.getRegClass(R)) 0
1590 continue; 0
1591 if (!HBS::isTransparentCopy(R, Inp, MRI)) 0
1592 continue; 0
1593 if (!HBS::isEqual(InpRC, B, RC, 0, W)) 0
1594 continue; 0
1595 Out.Reg = R; 0
1596 Out.Sub = 0; 0
1597 return true; 0
1598 } ----
1599 // Check if there is a super-register, whose part (with a subregister) ----
1600 // is equal to the input. ----
1601 // Only do double registers for now. ----
1602 if (W*2 != RW) 0
1603 continue; 0
1604 if (MRI.getRegClass(R) != &Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass) 0
1605 continue; 0
1606 ----
1607 if (HBS::isEqual(InpRC, B, RC, 0, W)) 0
1608 Out.Sub = Hexagon::isub_lo; 0
1609 else if (HBS::isEqual(InpRC, B, RC, W, W)) 0
1610 Out.Sub = Hexagon::isub_hi; 0
1611 else ----
1612 continue; 0
1613 Out.Reg = R; 0
1614 if (HBS::isTransparentCopy(Out, Inp, MRI)) 0
1615 return true; 0
1616 } ----
1617 return false; 0
1618 } ----
1619 ----
1620 bool CopyGeneration::processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, 0
1621 const RegisterSet &AVs) { ----
1622 if (!BT.reached(&B)) 0
1623 return false; 0
1624 RegisterSet AVB(AVs); 0
1625 bool Changed = false; 0
1626 RegisterSet Defs; 0
1627 ----
1628 for (auto I = B.begin(), E = B.end(); I != E; ++I, AVB.insert(Defs)) { 0
1629 Defs.clear(); 0
1630 HBS::getInstrDefs(*I, Defs); 0
1631 ----
1632 unsigned Opc = I->getOpcode(); 0
1633 if (CopyPropagation::isCopyReg(Opc, false) || 0
1634 ConstGeneration::isTfrConst(*I)) 0
1635 continue; 0
1636 ----
1637 DebugLoc DL = I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1638 auto At = I->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() : I; 0
1639 ----
1640 for (Register R = Defs.find_first(); R; R = Defs.find_next(R)) { 0
1641 BitTracker::RegisterRef MR; 0
1642 auto *FRC = HBS::getFinalVRegClass(R, MRI); 0
1643 ----
1644 if (findMatch(R, MR, AVB)) { 0
1645 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(FRC); 0
1646 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(TargetOpcode::COPY), NewR) 0
1647 .addReg(MR.Reg, 0, MR.Sub); 0
1648 BT.put(BitTracker::RegisterRef(NewR), BT.get(MR)); 0
1649 HBS::replaceReg(R, NewR, MRI); 0
1650 Forbidden.insert(R); 0
1651 continue; 0
1652 } 0
1653 ----
1654 if (FRC == &Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass || 0
1655 FRC == &Hexagon::HvxWRRegClass) { ----
1656 // Try to generate REG_SEQUENCE. ----
1657 unsigned SubLo = HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(*FRC, Hexagon::ps_sub_lo); 0
1658 unsigned SubHi = HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(*FRC, Hexagon::ps_sub_hi); 0
1659 BitTracker::RegisterRef TL = { R, SubLo }; 0
1660 BitTracker::RegisterRef TH = { R, SubHi }; 0
1661 BitTracker::RegisterRef ML, MH; 0
1662 if (findMatch(TL, ML, AVB) && findMatch(TH, MH, AVB)) { 0
1663 auto *FRC = HBS::getFinalVRegClass(R, MRI); 0
1664 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(FRC); 0
1665 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE), NewR) 0
1666 .addReg(ML.Reg, 0, ML.Sub) 0
1667 .addImm(SubLo) 0
1668 .addReg(MH.Reg, 0, MH.Sub) 0
1669 .addImm(SubHi); 0
1670 BT.put(BitTracker::RegisterRef(NewR), BT.get(R)); 0
1671 HBS::replaceReg(R, NewR, MRI); 0
1672 Forbidden.insert(R); 0
1673 } ----
1674 } ----
1675 } ----
1676 } 0
1677 ----
1678 return Changed; 0
1679 } 0
1680 ----
1681 bool CopyPropagation::isCopyReg(unsigned Opc, bool NoConv) { 0
1682 switch (Opc) { 0
1683 case TargetOpcode::COPY: 0
1684 case TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE: ----
1685 case Hexagon::A4_combineir: ----
1686 case Hexagon::A4_combineri: ----
1687 return true; 0
1688 case Hexagon::A2_tfr: 0
1689 case Hexagon::A2_tfrp: ----
1690 case Hexagon::A2_combinew: ----
1691 case Hexagon::V6_vcombine: ----
1692 return NoConv; 0
1693 default: 0
1694 break; 0
1695 } ----
1696 return false; 0
1697 } ----
1698 ----
1699 bool CopyPropagation::propagateRegCopy(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1700 bool Changed = false; 0
1701 unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode(); 0
1702 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD = MI.getOperand(0); 0
1703 assert(MI.getOperand(0).getSubReg() == 0); 0
1704 ----
1705 switch (Opc) { 0
1706 case TargetOpcode::COPY: 0
1707 case Hexagon::A2_tfr: ----
1708 case Hexagon::A2_tfrp: { ----
1709 BitTracker::RegisterRef RS = MI.getOperand(1); 0
1710 if (!HBS::isTransparentCopy(RD, RS, MRI)) 0
1711 break; 0
1712 if (RS.Sub != 0) 0
1713 Changed = HBS::replaceRegWithSub(RD.Reg, RS.Reg, RS.Sub, MRI); 0
1714 else ----
1715 Changed = HBS::replaceReg(RD.Reg, RS.Reg, MRI); 0
1716 break; 0
1717 } ----
1718 case TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE: { 0
1719 BitTracker::RegisterRef SL, SH; 0
1720 if (HBS::parseRegSequence(MI, SL, SH, MRI)) { 0
1721 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI.getRegClass(RD.Reg); 0
1722 unsigned SubLo = HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(RC, Hexagon::ps_sub_lo); 0
1723 unsigned SubHi = HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(RC, Hexagon::ps_sub_hi); 0
1724 Changed = HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, SubLo, SL.Reg, SL.Sub, MRI); 0
1725 Changed |= HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, SubHi, SH.Reg, SH.Sub, MRI); 0
1726 } ----
1727 break; 0
1728 } ----
1729 case Hexagon::A2_combinew: 0
1730 case Hexagon::V6_vcombine: { ----
1731 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI.getRegClass(RD.Reg); 0
1732 unsigned SubLo = HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(RC, Hexagon::ps_sub_lo); 0
1733 unsigned SubHi = HRI.getHexagonSubRegIndex(RC, Hexagon::ps_sub_hi); 0
1734 BitTracker::RegisterRef RH = MI.getOperand(1), RL = MI.getOperand(2); 0
1735 Changed = HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, SubLo, RL.Reg, RL.Sub, MRI); 0
1736 Changed |= HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, SubHi, RH.Reg, RH.Sub, MRI); 0
1737 break; 0
1738 } ----
1739 case Hexagon::A4_combineir: 0
1740 case Hexagon::A4_combineri: { ----
1741 unsigned SrcX = (Opc == Hexagon::A4_combineir) ? 2 : 1; 0
1742 unsigned Sub = (Opc == Hexagon::A4_combineir) ? Hexagon::isub_lo 0
1743 : Hexagon::isub_hi; ----
1744 BitTracker::RegisterRef RS = MI.getOperand(SrcX); 0
1745 Changed = HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, Sub, RS.Reg, RS.Sub, MRI); 0
1746 break; 0
1747 } ----
1748 } ----
1749 return Changed; 0
1750 } ----
1751 ----
1752 bool CopyPropagation::processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, const RegisterSet&) { 0
1753 std::vector Instrs; 0
1754 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::reverse(B)) 0
1755 Instrs.push_back(&MI); 0
1756 ----
1757 bool Changed = false; 0
1758 for (auto *I : Instrs) { 0
1759 unsigned Opc = I->getOpcode(); 0
1760 if (!CopyPropagation::isCopyReg(Opc, true)) 0
1761 continue; 0
1762 Changed |= propagateRegCopy(*I); 0
1763 } ----
1764 ----
1765 return Changed; 0
1766 } 0

1770 // Recognize patterns that can be simplified and replace them with the ----
1771 // simpler forms. ----
1772 // This is by no means complete ----
1773 class BitSimplification : public Transformation { ----
1774 public: ----
1775 BitSimplification(BitTracker &bt, const MachineDominatorTree &mdt, 0
1776 const HexagonInstrInfo &hii, const HexagonRegisterInfo &hri, ----
1777 MachineRegisterInfo &mri, MachineFunction &mf) ----
1778 : Transformation(true), MDT(mdt), HII(hii), HRI(hri), MRI(mri), 0
1779 MF(mf), BT(bt) {} 0
1780 ----
1781 bool processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, const RegisterSet &AVs) override; ----
1782 ----
1783 private: ----
1784 struct RegHalf : public BitTracker::RegisterRef { ----
1785 bool Low; // Low/High halfword. ----
1786 }; ----
1787 ----
1788 bool matchHalf(unsigned SelfR, const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC, ----
1789 unsigned B, RegHalf &RH); ----
1790 bool validateReg(BitTracker::RegisterRef R, unsigned Opc, unsigned OpNum); ----
1791 ----

1797 bool genStoreImmediate(MachineInstr *MI); ----

1799 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC); ----

1801 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC); ----

1803 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC); ----

1805 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC); ----

1807 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC, const RegisterSet &AVs); ----

1814 // Cache of created instructions to avoid creating duplicates. ----
1815 // XXX Currently only used by genBitSplit. ----
1816 std::vector NewMIs; ----
1817 ----
