1827 ----
1828 // Check if the bits [B..B+16) in register cell RC form a valid halfword, ----
1829 // i.e. [0..16), [16..32), etc. of some register. If so, return true and ----
1830 // set the information about the found register in RH. ----
1831 bool BitSimplification::matchHalf(unsigned SelfR, 0
1832 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC, unsigned B, RegHalf &RH) { ----
1833 // XXX This could be searching in the set of available registers, in case ----
1834 // the match is not exact. ----
1835 ----
1836 // Match 16-bit chunks, where the RC[B..B+15] references exactly one ----
1837 // register and all the bits B..B+15 match between RC and the register. ----
1838 // This is meant to match "v1[0-15]", where v1 = { [0]:0 [1-15]:v1... }, ----
1839 // and RC = { [0]:0 [1-15]:v1[1-15]... }. ----
1840 bool Low = false; 0
1841 unsigned I = B; 0
1842 while (I < B+16 && RC[I].num()) 0
1843 I++; 0
1844 if (I == B+16) 0
1845 return false; 0
1846 ----
1847 Register Reg = RC[I].RefI.Reg; 0
1848 unsigned P = RC[I].RefI.Pos; // The RefI.Pos will be advanced by I-B. 0
1849 if (P < I-B) 0
1850 return false; 0
1851 unsigned Pos = P - (I-B); 0
1852 ----
1853 if (Reg == 0 || Reg == SelfR) // Don't match "self". 0
1854 return false; 0
1855 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
1856 return false; 0
1857 if (!BT.has(Reg)) 0
1858 return false; 0
1859 ----
1860 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &SC = BT.lookup(Reg); 0
1861 if (Pos+16 > SC.width()) 0
1862 return false; 0
1863 ----
1864 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 16; ++i) { 0
1865 const BitTracker::BitValue &RV = RC[i+B]; 0
1866 if (RV.Type == BitTracker::BitValue::Ref) { 0
1867 if (RV.RefI.Reg != Reg) 0
1868 return false; 0
1869 if (RV.RefI.Pos != i+Pos) 0
1870 return false; 0
1871 continue; 0
1872 } ----
1873 if (RC[i+B] != SC[i+Pos]) 0
1874 return false; 0
1875 } ----
1876 ----
1877 unsigned Sub = 0; 0
1878 switch (Pos) { 0
1879 case 0: 0
1880 Sub = Hexagon::isub_lo; 0
1881 Low = true; 0
1882 break; 0
1883 case 16: 0
1884 Sub = Hexagon::isub_lo; 0
1885 Low = false; 0
1886 break; 0
1887 case 32: 0
1888 Sub = Hexagon::isub_hi; 0
1889 Low = true; 0
1890 break; 0
1891 case 48: 0
1892 Sub = Hexagon::isub_hi; 0
1893 Low = false; 0
1894 break; 0
1895 default: 0
1896 return false; 0
1897 } ----
1898 ----
1899 RH.Reg = Reg; 0
1900 RH.Sub = Sub; 0
1901 RH.Low = Low; 0
1902 // If the subregister is not valid with the register, set it to 0. ----
1903 if (!HBS::getFinalVRegClass(RH, MRI)) 0
1904 RH.Sub = 0; 0
1905 ----
1906 return true; 0
1907 } ----
1908 ----
1909 bool BitSimplification::validateReg(BitTracker::RegisterRef R, unsigned Opc, 0
1910 unsigned OpNum) { ----
1911 auto *OpRC = HII.getRegClass(HII.get(Opc), OpNum, &HRI, MF); 0
1912 auto *RRC = HBS::getFinalVRegClass(R, MRI); 0
1913 return OpRC->hasSubClassEq(RRC); 0
1914 } ----
1915 ----
1916 // Check if RC matches the pattern of a S2_packhl. If so, return true and ----
1917 // set the inputs Rs and Rt. ----
1918 bool BitSimplification::matchPackhl(unsigned SelfR, 0
1919 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC, BitTracker::RegisterRef &Rs, ----
1920 BitTracker::RegisterRef &Rt) { ----
1921 RegHalf L1, H1, L2, H2; 0
1922 ----
1923 if (!matchHalf(SelfR, RC, 0, L2) || !matchHalf(SelfR, RC, 16, L1)) 0
1924 return false; 0
1925 if (!matchHalf(SelfR, RC, 32, H2) || !matchHalf(SelfR, RC, 48, H1)) 0
1926 return false; 0
1927 ----
1928 // Rs = H1.L1, Rt = H2.L2 ----
1929 if (H1.Reg != L1.Reg || H1.Sub != L1.Sub || H1.Low || !L1.Low) 0
1930 return false; 0
1931 if (H2.Reg != L2.Reg || H2.Sub != L2.Sub || H2.Low || !L2.Low) 0
1932 return false; 0
1933 ----
1934 Rs = H1; 0
1935 Rt = H2; 0
1936 return true; 0
1937 } ----
1938 ----
1939 unsigned BitSimplification::getCombineOpcode(bool HLow, bool LLow) { 0
1940 return HLow ? LLow ? Hexagon::A2_combine_ll 0
1941 : Hexagon::A2_combine_lh ----
1942 : LLow ? Hexagon::A2_combine_hl ----
1943 : Hexagon::A2_combine_hh; 0
1944 } ----
1945 ----
1946 // If MI stores the upper halfword of a register (potentially obtained via ----
1947 // shifts or extracts), replace it with a storerf instruction. This could ----
1948 // cause the "extraction" code to become dead. ----
1949 bool BitSimplification::genStoreUpperHalf(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1950 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1951 if (Opc != Hexagon::S2_storerh_io) 0
1952 return false; 0
1953 ----
1954 MachineOperand &ValOp = MI->getOperand(2); 0
1955 BitTracker::RegisterRef RS = ValOp; 0
1956 if (!BT.has(RS.Reg)) 0
1957 return false; 0
1958 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC = BT.lookup(RS.Reg); 0
1959 RegHalf H; 0
1960 if (!matchHalf(0, RC, 0, H)) 0
1961 return false; 0
1962 if (H.Low) 0
1963 return false; 0
1964 MI->setDesc(HII.get(Hexagon::S2_storerf_io)); 0
1965 ValOp.setReg(H.Reg); 0
1966 ValOp.setSubReg(H.Sub); 0
1967 return true; 0
1968 } ----
1969 ----
1970 // If MI stores a value known at compile-time, and the value is within a range ----
1971 // that avoids using constant-extenders, replace it with a store-immediate. ----
1972 bool BitSimplification::genStoreImmediate(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1973 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1974 unsigned Align = 0; 0
1975 switch (Opc) { 0
1976 case Hexagon::S2_storeri_io: 0
1977 Align++; 0
1978 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1979 case Hexagon::S2_storerh_io: 0
1980 Align++; 0
1981 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1982 case Hexagon::S2_storerb_io: 0
1983 break; 0
1984 default: 0
1985 return false; 0
1986 } ----
1987 ----
1988 // Avoid stores to frame-indices (due to an unknown offset). ----
1989 if (!MI->getOperand(0).isReg()) 0
1990 return false; 0
1991 MachineOperand &OffOp = MI->getOperand(1); 0
1992 if (!OffOp.isImm()) 0
1993 return false; 0
1994 ----
1995 int64_t Off = OffOp.getImm(); 0
1996 // Offset is u6:a. Sadly, there is no isShiftedUInt(n,x). ----
1997 if (!isUIntN(6+Align, Off) || (Off & ((1< 0
1998 return false; 0
1999 // Source register: ----
2000 BitTracker::RegisterRef RS = MI->getOperand(2); 0
2001 if (!BT.has(RS.Reg)) 0
2002 return false; 0
2003 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC = BT.lookup(RS.Reg); 0
2004 uint64_t U; ----
2005 if (!HBS::getConst(RC, 0, RC.width(), U)) 0
2006 return false; 0
2007 ----
2008 // Only consider 8-bit values to avoid constant-extenders. ----
2009 int V; ----
2010 switch (Opc) { 0
2011 case Hexagon::S2_storerb_io: 0
2012 V = int8_t(U); 0
2013 break; 0
2014 case Hexagon::S2_storerh_io: 0
2015 V = int16_t(U); 0
2016 break; 0
2017 case Hexagon::S2_storeri_io: 0
2018 V = int32_t(U); 0
2019 break; 0
2020 default: 0
2021 // Opc is already checked above to be one of the three store instructions. ----
2022 // This silences a -Wuninitialized false positive on GCC 5.4. ----
2023 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected store opcode"); 0
2024 } ----
2025 if (!isInt<8>(V)) 0
2026 return false; 0
2027 ----
2028 MI->removeOperand(2); 0
2029 switch (Opc) { 0
2030 case Hexagon::S2_storerb_io: 0
2031 MI->setDesc(HII.get(Hexagon::S4_storeirb_io)); 0
2032 break; 0
2033 case Hexagon::S2_storerh_io: 0
2034 MI->setDesc(HII.get(Hexagon::S4_storeirh_io)); 0
2035 break; 0
2036 case Hexagon::S2_storeri_io: 0
2037 MI->setDesc(HII.get(Hexagon::S4_storeiri_io)); 0
2038 break; 0
2039 } ----
2040 MI->addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateImm(V)); 0
2041 return true; 0
2042 } ----
2043 ----
2044 // If MI is equivalent o S2_packhl, generate the S2_packhl. MI could be the ----
2045 // last instruction in a sequence that results in something equivalent to ----
2046 // the pack-halfwords. The intent is to cause the entire sequence to become ----
2047 // dead. ----
2048 bool BitSimplification::genPackhl(MachineInstr *MI, 0
2049 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD, const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC) { ----
2050 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
2051 if (Opc == Hexagon::S2_packhl) 0
2052 return false; 0
2053 BitTracker::RegisterRef Rs, Rt; 0
2054 if (!matchPackhl(RD.Reg, RC, Rs, Rt)) 0
2055 return false; 0
2056 if (!validateReg(Rs, Hexagon::S2_packhl, 1) || 0
2057 !validateReg(Rt, Hexagon::S2_packhl, 2)) 0
2058 return false; 0
2059 ----
2060 MachineBasicBlock &B = *MI->getParent(); 0
2061 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass); 0
2062 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2063 auto At = MI->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() 0
2064 : MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI); 0
2065 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::S2_packhl), NewR) 0
2066 .addReg(Rs.Reg, 0, Rs.Sub) 0
2067 .addReg(Rt.Reg, 0, Rt.Sub); 0
2068 HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, RD.Sub, NewR, 0, MRI); 0
2069 BT.put(BitTracker::RegisterRef(NewR), RC); 0
2070 return true; 0
2071 } 0
2072 ----
2073 // If MI produces halfword of the input in the low half of the output, ----
2074 // replace it with zero-extend or extractu. ----
2075 bool BitSimplification::genExtractHalf(MachineInstr *MI, 0
2076 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD, const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC) { ----
2077 RegHalf L; 0
2078 // Check for halfword in low 16 bits, zeros elsewhere. ----
2079 if (!matchHalf(RD.Reg, RC, 0, L) || !HBS::isZero(RC, 16, 16)) 0
2080 return false; 0
2081 ----
2082 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
2083 MachineBasicBlock &B = *MI->getParent(); 0
2084 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2085 ----
2086 // Prefer zxth, since zxth can go in any slot, while extractu only in ----
2087 // slots 2 and 3. ----
2088 unsigned NewR = 0; 0
2089 auto At = MI->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() 0
2090 : MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI); 0
2091 if (L.Low && Opc != Hexagon::A2_zxth) { 0
2092 if (validateReg(L, Hexagon::A2_zxth, 1)) { 0
2093 NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass); 0
2094 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::A2_zxth), NewR) 0
2095 .addReg(L.Reg, 0, L.Sub); 0
2096 } ----
2097 } else if (!L.Low && Opc != Hexagon::S2_lsr_i_r) { 0
2098 if (validateReg(L, Hexagon::S2_lsr_i_r, 1)) { 0
2099 NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass); 0
2100 BuildMI(B, MI, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::S2_lsr_i_r), NewR) 0
2101 .addReg(L.Reg, 0, L.Sub) 0
2102 .addImm(16); 0
2103 } ----
2104 } ----
2105 if (NewR == 0) 0
2106 return false; 0
2107 HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, RD.Sub, NewR, 0, MRI); 0
2108 BT.put(BitTracker::RegisterRef(NewR), RC); 0
2109 return true; 0
2110 } 0
2111 ----
2112 // If MI is equivalent to a combine(.L/.H, .L/.H) replace with with the ----
2113 // combine. ----
2114 bool BitSimplification::genCombineHalf(MachineInstr *MI, 0
2115 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD, const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC) { ----
2116 RegHalf L, H; 0
2117 // Check for combine h/l ----
2118 if (!matchHalf(RD.Reg, RC, 0, L) || !matchHalf(RD.Reg, RC, 16, H)) 0
2119 return false; 0
2120 // Do nothing if this is just a reg copy. ----
2121 if (L.Reg == H.Reg && L.Sub == H.Sub && !H.Low && L.Low) 0
2122 return false; 0
2123 ----
2124 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
2125 unsigned COpc = getCombineOpcode(H.Low, L.Low); 0
2126 if (COpc == Opc) 0
2127 return false; 0
2128 if (!validateReg(H, COpc, 1) || !validateReg(L, COpc, 2)) 0
2129 return false; 0
2130 ----
2131 MachineBasicBlock &B = *MI->getParent(); 0
2132 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2133 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass); 0
2134 auto At = MI->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() 0
2135 : MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI); 0
2136 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(COpc), NewR) 0
2137 .addReg(H.Reg, 0, H.Sub) 0
2138 .addReg(L.Reg, 0, L.Sub); 0
2139 HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, RD.Sub, NewR, 0, MRI); 0
2140 BT.put(BitTracker::RegisterRef(NewR), RC); 0
2141 return true; 0
2142 } 0
2143 ----
2144 // If MI resets high bits of a register and keeps the lower ones, replace it ----
2145 // with zero-extend byte/half, and-immediate, or extractu, as appropriate. ----
2146 bool BitSimplification::genExtractLow(MachineInstr *MI, 0
2147 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD, const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC) { ----
2148 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
2149 switch (Opc) { 0
2150 case Hexagon::A2_zxtb: 0
2151 case Hexagon::A2_zxth: ----
2152 case Hexagon::S2_extractu: ----
2153 return false; 0
2154 } ----
2155 if (Opc == Hexagon::A2_andir && MI->getOperand(2).isImm()) { 0
2156 int32_t Imm = MI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
2157 if (isInt<10>(Imm)) 0
2158 return false; 0
2159 } ----
2160 ----
2161 if (MI->hasUnmodeledSideEffects() || MI->isInlineAsm()) 0
2162 return false; 0
2163 unsigned W = RC.width(); 0
2164 while (W > 0 && RC[W-1].is(0)) 0
2165 W--; 0
2166 if (W == 0 || W == RC.width()) 0
2167 return false; 0
2168 unsigned NewOpc = (W == 8) ? Hexagon::A2_zxtb 0
2169 : (W == 16) ? Hexagon::A2_zxth ----
2170 : (W < 10) ? Hexagon::A2_andir ----
2171 : Hexagon::S2_extractu; ----
2172 MachineBasicBlock &B = *MI->getParent(); 0
2173 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2174 ----
2175 for (auto &Op : MI->uses()) { 0
2176 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
2177 continue; 0
2178 BitTracker::RegisterRef RS = Op; 0
2179 if (!BT.has(RS.Reg)) 0
2180 continue; 0
2181 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &SC = BT.lookup(RS.Reg); 0
2182 unsigned BN, BW; ----
2183 if (!HBS::getSubregMask(RS, BN, BW, MRI)) 0
2184 continue; 0
2185 if (BW < W || !HBS::isEqual(RC, 0, SC, BN, W)) 0
2186 continue; 0
2187 if (!validateReg(RS, NewOpc, 1)) 0
2188 continue; 0
2189 ----
2190 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass); 0
2191 auto At = MI->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() 0
2192 : MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI); 0
2193 auto MIB = BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(NewOpc), NewR) 0
2194 .addReg(RS.Reg, 0, RS.Sub); 0
2195 if (NewOpc == Hexagon::A2_andir) 0
2196 MIB.addImm((1 << W) - 1); 0
2197 else if (NewOpc == Hexagon::S2_extractu) 0
2198 MIB.addImm(W).addImm(0); 0
2199 HBS::replaceSubWithSub(RD.Reg, RD.Sub, NewR, 0, MRI); 0
2200 BT.put(BitTracker::RegisterRef(NewR), RC); 0
2201 return true; 0
2202 } ----
2203 return false; 0
2204 } ----
2205 ----
2206 bool BitSimplification::genBitSplit(MachineInstr *MI, 0
2207 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD, const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC, ----
2208 const RegisterSet &AVs) { ----
2209 if (!GenBitSplit) 0
2210 return false; 0
2211 if (MaxBitSplit.getNumOccurrences()) { 0
2212 if (CountBitSplit >= MaxBitSplit) 0
2213 return false; 0
2214 } ----
2215 ----
2216 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
2217 switch (Opc) { 0
2218 case Hexagon::A4_bitsplit: 0
2219 case Hexagon::A4_bitspliti: ----
2220 return false; 0
2221 } ----
2222 ----
2223 unsigned W = RC.width(); 0
2224 if (W != 32) 0
2225 return false; 0
2226 ----
2227 auto ctlz = [] (const BitTracker::RegisterCell &C) -> unsigned { 0
2228 unsigned Z = C.width(); 0
2229 while (Z > 0 && C[Z-1].is(0)) 0
2230 --Z; 0
2231 return C.width() - Z; 0
2232 }; ----
2233 ----
2234 // Count the number of leading zeros in the target RC. ----
2235 unsigned Z = ctlz(RC); 0
2236 if (Z == 0 || Z == W) 0
2237 return false; 0
2238 ----
2239 // A simplistic analysis: assume the source register (the one being split) ----
2240 // is fully unknown, and that all its bits are self-references. ----
2241 const BitTracker::BitValue &B0 = RC[0]; 0
2242 if (B0.Type != BitTracker::BitValue::Ref) 0
2243 return false; 0
2244 ----
2245 unsigned SrcR = B0.RefI.Reg; 0
2246 unsigned SrcSR = 0; 0
2247 unsigned Pos = B0.RefI.Pos; 0
2248 ----
2249 // All the non-zero bits should be consecutive bits from the same register. ----
2250 for (unsigned i = 1; i < W-Z; ++i) { 0
2251 const BitTracker::BitValue &V = RC[i]; 0
2252 if (V.Type != BitTracker::BitValue::Ref) 0
2253 return false; 0
2254 if (V.RefI.Reg != SrcR || V.RefI.Pos != Pos+i) 0
2255 return false; 0
2256 } ----
2257 ----
2258 // Now, find the other bitfield among AVs. ----
2259 for (unsigned S = AVs.find_first(); S; S = AVs.find_next(S)) { 0
2260 // The number of leading zeros here should be the number of trailing ----
2261 // non-zeros in RC. ----
2262 unsigned SRC = MRI.getRegClass(S)->getID(); 0
2263 if (SRC != Hexagon::IntRegsRegClassID && 0
2264 SRC != Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClassID) ----
2265 continue; 0
2266 if (!BT.has(S)) 0
2267 continue; 0
2268 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &SC = BT.lookup(S); 0
2269 if (SC.width() != W || ctlz(SC) != W-Z) 0
2270 continue; 0
2271 // The Z lower bits should now match SrcR. ----
2272 const BitTracker::BitValue &S0 = SC[0]; 0
2273 if (S0.Type != BitTracker::BitValue::Ref || S0.RefI.Reg != SrcR) 0
2274 continue; 0
2275 unsigned P = S0.RefI.Pos; 0
2276 ----
2277 if (Pos <= P && (Pos + W-Z) != P) 0
2278 continue; 0
2279 if (P < Pos && (P + Z) != Pos) 0
2280 continue; 0
2281 // The starting bitfield position must be at a subregister boundary. ----
2282 if (std::min(P, Pos) != 0 && std::min(P, Pos) != 32) 0
2283 continue; 0
2284 ----
2285 unsigned I; ----
2286 for (I = 1; I < Z; ++I) { 0
2287 const BitTracker::BitValue &V = SC[I]; 0
2288 if (V.Type != BitTracker::BitValue::Ref) 0
2289 break; 0
2290 if (V.RefI.Reg != SrcR || V.RefI.Pos != P+I) 0
2291 break; 0
2292 } ----
2293 if (I != Z) 0
2294 continue; 0
2295 ----
2296 // Generate bitsplit where S is defined. ----
2297 if (MaxBitSplit.getNumOccurrences()) 0
2298 CountBitSplit++; 0
2299 MachineInstr *DefS = MRI.getVRegDef(S); 0
2300 assert(DefS != nullptr); 0
2301 DebugLoc DL = DefS->getDebugLoc(); 0
2302 MachineBasicBlock &B = *DefS->getParent(); 0
2303 auto At = DefS->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() 0
2304 : MachineBasicBlock::iterator(DefS); 0
2305 if (MRI.getRegClass(SrcR)->getID() == Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClassID) 0
2306 SrcSR = (std::min(Pos, P) == 32) ? Hexagon::isub_hi : Hexagon::isub_lo; 0
2307 if (!validateReg({SrcR,SrcSR}, Hexagon::A4_bitspliti, 1)) 0
2308 continue; 0
2309 unsigned ImmOp = Pos <= P ? W-Z : Z; 0
2310 ----
2311 // Find an existing bitsplit instruction if one already exists. ----
2312 unsigned NewR = 0; 0
2313 for (MachineInstr *In : NewMIs) { 0
2314 if (In->getOpcode() != Hexagon::A4_bitspliti) 0
2315 continue; 0
2316 MachineOperand &Op1 = In->getOperand(1); 0
2317 if (Op1.getReg() != SrcR || Op1.getSubReg() != SrcSR) 0
2318 continue; 0
2319 if (In->getOperand(2).getImm() != ImmOp) 0
2320 continue; 0
2321 // Check if the target register is available here. ----
2322 MachineOperand &Op0 = In->getOperand(0); 0
2323 MachineInstr *DefI = MRI.getVRegDef(Op0.getReg()); 0
2324 assert(DefI != nullptr); 0
2325 if (!MDT.dominates(DefI, &*At)) 0
2326 continue; 0
2327 ----
2328 // Found one that can be reused. ----
2329 assert(Op0.getSubReg() == 0); 0
2330 NewR = Op0.getReg(); 0
2331 break; 0
2332 } ----
2333 if (!NewR) { 0
2334 NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass); 0
2335 auto NewBS = BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::A4_bitspliti), NewR) 0
2336 .addReg(SrcR, 0, SrcSR) 0
2337 .addImm(ImmOp); 0
2338 NewMIs.push_back(NewBS); 0
2339 } ----
2340 if (Pos <= P) { 0
2341 HBS::replaceRegWithSub(RD.Reg, NewR, Hexagon::isub_lo, MRI); 0
2342 HBS::replaceRegWithSub(S, NewR, Hexagon::isub_hi, MRI); 0
2343 } else { ----
2344 HBS::replaceRegWithSub(S, NewR, Hexagon::isub_lo, MRI); 0
2345 HBS::replaceRegWithSub(RD.Reg, NewR, Hexagon::isub_hi, MRI); 0
2346 } ----
2347 return true; 0
2348 } 0
2349 ----
2350 return false; 0
2351 } ----
2352 ----
2353 // Check for tstbit simplification opportunity, where the bit being checked ----
2354 // can be tracked back to another register. For example: ----
2355 // %2 = S2_lsr_i_r %1, 5 ----
2356 // %3 = S2_tstbit_i %2, 0 ----
2357 // => ----
2358 // %3 = S2_tstbit_i %1, 5 ----
2359 bool BitSimplification::simplifyTstbit(MachineInstr *MI, 0
2360 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD, const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC) { ----
2361 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
2362 if (Opc != Hexagon::S2_tstbit_i) 0
2363 return false; 0
2364 ----
2365 unsigned BN = MI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
2366 BitTracker::RegisterRef RS = MI->getOperand(1); 0
2367 unsigned F, W; ----
2368 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2369 if (!BT.has(RS.Reg) || !HBS::getSubregMask(RS, F, W, MRI)) 0
2370 return false; 0
2371 MachineBasicBlock &B = *MI->getParent(); 0
2372 auto At = MI->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() 0
2373 : MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI); 0
2374 ----
2375 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &SC = BT.lookup(RS.Reg); 0
2376 const BitTracker::BitValue &V = SC[F+BN]; 0
2377 if (V.Type == BitTracker::BitValue::Ref && V.RefI.Reg != RS.Reg) { 0
2378 const TargetRegisterClass *TC = MRI.getRegClass(V.RefI.Reg); 0
2379 // Need to map V.RefI.Reg to a 32-bit register, i.e. if it is ----
2380 // a double register, need to use a subregister and adjust bit ----
2381 // number. ----
2382 unsigned P = std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
2383 BitTracker::RegisterRef RR(V.RefI.Reg, 0); 0
2384 if (TC == &Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass) { 0
2385 P = V.RefI.Pos; 0
2386 RR.Sub = Hexagon::isub_lo; 0
2387 if (P >= 32) { 0
2388 P -= 32; 0
2389 RR.Sub = Hexagon::isub_hi; 0
2390 } ----
2391 } else if (TC == &Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass) { 0
2392 P = V.RefI.Pos; 0
2393 } ----
2394 if (P != std::numeric_limits::max()) { 0
2395 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::PredRegsRegClass); 0
2396 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::S2_tstbit_i), NewR) 0
2397 .addReg(RR.Reg, 0, RR.Sub) 0
2398 .addImm(P); 0
2399 HBS::replaceReg(RD.Reg, NewR, MRI); 0
2400 BT.put(NewR, RC); 0
2401 return true; 0
2402 } ----
2403 } else if (V.is(0) || V.is(1)) { 0
2404 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::PredRegsRegClass); 0
2405 unsigned NewOpc = V.is(0) ? Hexagon::PS_false : Hexagon::PS_true; 0
2406 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(NewOpc), NewR); 0
2407 HBS::replaceReg(RD.Reg, NewR, MRI); 0
2408 return true; 0
2409 } ----
2410 ----
2411 return false; 0
2412 } 0
2413 ----
2414 // Detect whether RD is a bitfield extract (sign- or zero-extended) of ----
2415 // some register from the AVs set. Create a new corresponding instruction ----
2416 // at the location of MI. The intent is to recognize situations where ----
2417 // a sequence of instructions performs an operation that is equivalent to ----
2418 // an extract operation, such as a shift left followed by a shift right. ----
2419 bool BitSimplification::simplifyExtractLow(MachineInstr *MI, 0
2420 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD, const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC, ----
2421 const RegisterSet &AVs) { ----
2422 if (!GenExtract) 0
2423 return false; 0
2424 if (MaxExtract.getNumOccurrences()) { 0
2425 if (CountExtract >= MaxExtract) 0
2426 return false; 0
2427 CountExtract++; 0
2428 } ----
2429 ----
2430 unsigned W = RC.width(); 0
2431 unsigned RW = W; 0
2432 unsigned Len; ----
2433 bool Signed; ----
2434 ----
2435 // The code is mostly class-independent, except for the part that generates ----
2436 // the extract instruction, and establishes the source register (in case it ----
2437 // needs to use a subregister). ----
2438 const TargetRegisterClass *FRC = HBS::getFinalVRegClass(RD, MRI); 0
2439 if (FRC != &Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass && FRC != &Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass) 0
2440 return false; 0
2441 assert(RD.Sub == 0); 0
2442 ----
2443 // Observation: ----
2444 // If the cell has a form of 00..0xx..x with k zeros and n remaining ----
2445 // bits, this could be an extractu of the n bits, but it could also be ----
2446 // an extractu of a longer field which happens to have 0s in the top ----
2447 // bit positions. ----
2448 // The same logic applies to sign-extended fields. ----
2449 // ----
2450 // Do not check for the extended extracts, since it would expand the ----
2451 // search space quite a bit. The search may be expensive as it is. ----
2452 ----
2453 const BitTracker::BitValue &TopV = RC[W-1]; 0
2454 ----
2455 // Eliminate candidates that have self-referential bits, since they ----
2456 // cannot be extracts from other registers. Also, skip registers that ----
2457 // have compile-time constant values. ----
2458 bool IsConst = true; 0
2459 for (unsigned I = 0; I != W; ++I) { 0
2460 const BitTracker::BitValue &V = RC[I]; 0
2461 if (V.Type == BitTracker::BitValue::Ref && V.RefI.Reg == RD.Reg) 0
2462 return false; 0
2463 IsConst = IsConst && (V.is(0) || V.is(1)); 0
2464 } ----
2465 if (IsConst) 0
2466 return false; 0
2467 ----
2468 if (TopV.is(0) || TopV.is(1)) { 0
2469 bool S = TopV.is(1); 0
2470 for (--W; W > 0 && RC[W-1].is(S); --W) 0
2471 ; ----
2472 Len = W; 0
2473 Signed = S; 0
2474 // The sign bit must be a part of the field being extended. ----
2475 if (Signed) 0
2476 ++Len; 0
2477 } else { ----
2478 // This could still be a sign-extended extract. ----
2479 assert(TopV.Type == BitTracker::BitValue::Ref); 0
2480 if (TopV.RefI.Reg == RD.Reg || TopV.RefI.Pos == W-1) 0
2481 return false; 0
2482 for (--W; W > 0 && RC[W-1] == TopV; --W) 0
2483 ; ----
2484 // The top bits of RC are copies of TopV. One occurrence of TopV will ----
2485 // be a part of the field. ----
2486 Len = W + 1; 0
2487 Signed = true; 0
2488 } ----
2489 ----
2490 // This would be just a copy. It should be handled elsewhere. ----
2491 if (Len == RW) 0
2492 return false; 0
2493 ----
2494 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
2495 dbgs() << __func__ << " on reg: " << printReg(RD.Reg, &HRI, RD.Sub) ----
2496 << ", MI: " << *MI; ----
2497 dbgs() << "Cell: " << RC << '\n'; ----
2498 dbgs() << "Expected bitfield size: " << Len << " bits, " ----
2499 << (Signed ? "sign" : "zero") << "-extended\n"; ----
2500 }); ----
2501 ----
2502 bool Changed = false; 0
2503 ----
2504 for (unsigned R = AVs.find_first(); R != 0; R = AVs.find_next(R)) { 0
2505 if (!BT.has(R)) 0
2506 continue; 0
2507 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &SC = BT.lookup(R); 0
2508 unsigned SW = SC.width(); 0
2509 ----
2510 // The source can be longer than the destination, as long as its size is ----
2511 // a multiple of the size of the destination. Also, we would need to be ----
2512 // able to refer to the subregister in the source that would be of the ----
2513 // same size as the destination, but only check the sizes here. ----
2514 if (SW < RW || (SW % RW) != 0) 0
2515 continue; 0
2516 ----
2517 // The field can start at any offset in SC as long as it contains Len ----
2518 // bits and does not cross subregister boundary (if the source register ----
2519 // is longer than the destination). ----
2520 unsigned Off = 0; 0
2521 while (Off <= SW-Len) { 0
2522 unsigned OE = (Off+Len)/RW; 0
2523 if (OE != Off/RW) { 0
2524 // The assumption here is that if the source (R) is longer than the ----
2525 // destination, then the destination is a sequence of words of ----
2526 // size RW, and each such word in R can be accessed via a subregister. ----
2527 // ----
2528 // If the beginning and the end of the field cross the subregister ----
2529 // boundary, advance to the next subregister. ----
2530 Off = OE*RW; 0
2531 continue; 0
2532 } ----
2533 if (HBS::isEqual(RC, 0, SC, Off, Len)) 0
2534 break; 0
2535 ++Off; 0
2536 } ----
2537 ----
2538 if (Off > SW-Len) 0
2539 continue; 0
2540 ----
2541 // Found match. ----
2542 unsigned ExtOpc = 0; 0
2543 if (Off == 0) { 0
2544 if (Len == 8) 0
2545 ExtOpc = Signed ? Hexagon::A2_sxtb : Hexagon::A2_zxtb; 0
2546 else if (Len == 16) 0
2547 ExtOpc = Signed ? Hexagon::A2_sxth : Hexagon::A2_zxth; 0
2548 else if (Len < 10 && !Signed) 0
2549 ExtOpc = Hexagon::A2_andir; 0
2550 } ----
2551 if (ExtOpc == 0) { 0
2552 ExtOpc = 0
2553 Signed ? (RW == 32 ? Hexagon::S4_extract : Hexagon::S4_extractp) 0
2554 : (RW == 32 ? Hexagon::S2_extractu : Hexagon::S2_extractup); ----
2555 } ----
2556 unsigned SR = 0; 0
2557 // This only recognizes isub_lo and isub_hi. ----
2558 if (RW != SW && RW*2 != SW) 0
2559 continue; 0
2560 if (RW != SW) 0
2561 SR = (Off/RW == 0) ? Hexagon::isub_lo : Hexagon::isub_hi; 0
2562 Off = Off % RW; 0
2563 ----
2564 if (!validateReg({R,SR}, ExtOpc, 1)) 0
2565 continue; 0
2566 ----
2567 // Don't generate the same instruction as the one being optimized. ----
2568 if (MI->getOpcode() == ExtOpc) { 0
2569 // All possible ExtOpc's have the source in operand(1). ----
2570 const MachineOperand &SrcOp = MI->getOperand(1); 0
2571 if (SrcOp.getReg() == R) 0
2572 continue; 0
2573 } ----
2574 ----
2575 DebugLoc DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2576 MachineBasicBlock &B = *MI->getParent(); 0
2577 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(FRC); 0
2578 auto At = MI->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() 0
2579 : MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI); 0
2580 auto MIB = BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(ExtOpc), NewR) 0
2581 .addReg(R, 0, SR); 0
2582 switch (ExtOpc) { 0
2583 case Hexagon::A2_sxtb: 0
2584 case Hexagon::A2_zxtb: ----
2585 case Hexagon::A2_sxth: ----
2586 case Hexagon::A2_zxth: ----
2587 break; 0
2588 case Hexagon::A2_andir: 0
2589 MIB.addImm((1u << Len) - 1); 0
2590 break; 0
2591 case Hexagon::S4_extract: 0
2592 case Hexagon::S2_extractu: ----
2593 case Hexagon::S4_extractp: ----
2594 case Hexagon::S2_extractup: ----
2595 MIB.addImm(Len) 0
2596 .addImm(Off); 0
2597 break; 0
2598 default: 0
2599 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode"); 0
2600 } ----
2601 ----
2602 HBS::replaceReg(RD.Reg, NewR, MRI); 0
2603 BT.put(BitTracker::RegisterRef(NewR), RC); 0
2604 Changed = true; 0
2605 break; 0
2606 } 0
2607 ----
2608 return Changed; 0
2609 } ----
2610 ----
2611 bool BitSimplification::simplifyRCmp0(MachineInstr *MI, 0
2612 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD) { ----
2613 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
2614 if (Opc != Hexagon::A4_rcmpeqi && Opc != Hexagon::A4_rcmpneqi) 0
2615 return false; 0
2616 MachineOperand &CmpOp = MI->getOperand(2); 0
2617 if (!CmpOp.isImm() || CmpOp.getImm() != 0) 0
2618 return false; 0
2619 ----
2620 const TargetRegisterClass *FRC = HBS::getFinalVRegClass(RD, MRI); 0
2621 if (FRC != &Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass && FRC != &Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass) 0
2622 return false; 0
2623 assert(RD.Sub == 0); 0
2624 ----
2625 MachineBasicBlock &B = *MI->getParent(); 0
2626 const DebugLoc &DL = MI->getDebugLoc(); 0
2627 auto At = MI->isPHI() ? B.getFirstNonPHI() 0
2628 : MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI); 0
2629 bool KnownZ = true; 0
2630 bool KnownNZ = false; 0
2631 ----
2632 BitTracker::RegisterRef SR = MI->getOperand(1); 0
2633 if (!BT.has(SR.Reg)) 0
2634 return false; 0
2635 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &SC = BT.lookup(SR.Reg); 0
2636 unsigned F, W; ----
2637 if (!HBS::getSubregMask(SR, F, W, MRI)) 0
2638 return false; 0
2639 ----
2640 for (uint16_t I = F; I != F+W; ++I) { 0
2641 const BitTracker::BitValue &V = SC[I]; 0
2642 if (!V.is(0)) 0
2643 KnownZ = false; 0
2644 if (V.is(1)) 0
2645 KnownNZ = true; 0
2646 } ----
2647 ----
2648 auto ReplaceWithConst = [&](int C) { 0
2649 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(FRC); 0
2650 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::A2_tfrsi), NewR) 0
2651 .addImm(C); 0
2652 HBS::replaceReg(RD.Reg, NewR, MRI); 0
2653 BitTracker::RegisterCell NewRC(W); 0
2654 for (uint16_t I = 0; I != W; ++I) { 0
2655 NewRC[I] = BitTracker::BitValue(C & 1); 0
2656 C = unsigned(C) >> 1; 0
2657 } ----
2658 BT.put(BitTracker::RegisterRef(NewR), NewRC); 0
2659 return true; 0
2660 }; 0
2661 ----
2662 auto IsNonZero = [] (const MachineOperand &Op) { 0
2663 if (Op.isGlobal() || Op.isBlockAddress()) 0
2664 return true; 0
2665 if (Op.isImm()) 0
2666 return Op.getImm() != 0; 0
2667 if (Op.isCImm()) 0
2668 return !Op.getCImm()->isZero(); 0
2669 if (Op.isFPImm()) 0
2670 return !Op.getFPImm()->isZero(); 0
2671 return false; 0
2672 }; ----
2673 ----
2674 auto IsZero = [] (const MachineOperand &Op) { 0
2675 if (Op.isGlobal() || Op.isBlockAddress()) 0
2676 return false; 0
2677 if (Op.isImm()) 0
2678 return Op.getImm() == 0; 0
2679 if (Op.isCImm()) 0
2680 return Op.getCImm()->isZero(); 0
2681 if (Op.isFPImm()) 0
2682 return Op.getFPImm()->isZero(); 0
2683 return false; 0
2684 }; ----
2685 ----
2686 // If the source register is known to be 0 or non-0, the comparison can ----
2687 // be folded to a load of a constant. ----
2688 if (KnownZ || KnownNZ) { 0
2689 assert(KnownZ != KnownNZ && "Register cannot be both 0 and non-0"); 0
2690 return ReplaceWithConst(KnownZ == (Opc == Hexagon::A4_rcmpeqi)); 0
2691 } ----
2692 ----
2693 // Special case: if the compare comes from a C2_muxii, then we know the ----
2694 // two possible constants that can be the source value. ----
2695 MachineInstr *InpDef = MRI.getVRegDef(SR.Reg); 0
2696 if (!InpDef) 0
2697 return false; 0
2698 if (SR.Sub == 0 && InpDef->getOpcode() == Hexagon::C2_muxii) { 0
2699 MachineOperand &Src1 = InpDef->getOperand(2); 0
2700 MachineOperand &Src2 = InpDef->getOperand(3); 0
2701 // Check if both are non-zero. ----
2702 bool KnownNZ1 = IsNonZero(Src1), KnownNZ2 = IsNonZero(Src2); 0
2703 if (KnownNZ1 && KnownNZ2) 0
2704 return ReplaceWithConst(Opc == Hexagon::A4_rcmpneqi); 0
2705 // Check if both are zero. ----
2706 bool KnownZ1 = IsZero(Src1), KnownZ2 = IsZero(Src2); 0
2707 if (KnownZ1 && KnownZ2) 0
2708 return ReplaceWithConst(Opc == Hexagon::A4_rcmpeqi); 0
2709 ----
2710 // If for both operands we know that they are either 0 or non-0, ----
2711 // replace the comparison with a C2_muxii, using the same predicate ----
2712 // register, but with operands substituted with 0/1 accordingly. ----
2713 if ((KnownZ1 || KnownNZ1) && (KnownZ2 || KnownNZ2)) { 0
2714 Register NewR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(FRC); 0
2715 BuildMI(B, At, DL, HII.get(Hexagon::C2_muxii), NewR) 0
2716 .addReg(InpDef->getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
2717 .addImm(KnownZ1 == (Opc == Hexagon::A4_rcmpeqi)) 0
2718 .addImm(KnownZ2 == (Opc == Hexagon::A4_rcmpeqi)); 0
2719 HBS::replaceReg(RD.Reg, NewR, MRI); 0
2720 // Create a new cell with only the least significant bit unknown. ----
2721 BitTracker::RegisterCell NewRC(W); 0
2722 NewRC[0] = BitTracker::BitValue::self(); 0
2723 NewRC.fill(1, W, BitTracker::BitValue::Zero); 0
2724 BT.put(BitTracker::RegisterRef(NewR), NewRC); 0
2725 return true; 0
2726 } 0
2727 } ----
2728 ----
2729 return false; 0
2730 } ----
2731 ----
2732 bool BitSimplification::processBlock(MachineBasicBlock &B, 0
2733 const RegisterSet &AVs) { ----
2734 if (!BT.reached(&B)) 0
2735 return false; 0
2736 bool Changed = false; 0
2737 RegisterSet AVB = AVs; 0
2738 RegisterSet Defs; 0
2739 ----
2740 for (auto I = B.begin(), E = B.end(); I != E; ++I, AVB.insert(Defs)) { 0
2741 MachineInstr *MI = &*I; 0
2742 Defs.clear(); 0
2743 HBS::getInstrDefs(*MI, Defs); 0
2744 ----
2745 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
2746 if (Opc == TargetOpcode::COPY || Opc == TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE) 0
2747 continue; 0
2748 ----
2749 if (MI->mayStore()) { 0
2750 bool T = genStoreUpperHalf(MI); 0
2751 T = T || genStoreImmediate(MI); 0
2752 Changed |= T; 0
2753 continue; 0
2754 } 0
2755 ----
2756 if (Defs.count() != 1) 0
2757 continue; 0
2758 const MachineOperand &Op0 = MI->getOperand(0); 0
2759 if (!Op0.isReg() || !Op0.isDef()) 0
2760 continue; 0
2761 BitTracker::RegisterRef RD = Op0; 0
2762 if (!BT.has(RD.Reg)) 0
2763 continue; 0
2764 const TargetRegisterClass *FRC = HBS::getFinalVRegClass(RD, MRI); 0
2765 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC = BT.lookup(RD.Reg); 0
2766 ----
2767 if (FRC->getID() == Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClassID) { 0
2768 bool T = genPackhl(MI, RD, RC); 0
2769 T = T || simplifyExtractLow(MI, RD, RC, AVB); 0
2770 Changed |= T; 0
2771 continue; 0
2772 } 0
2773 ----
2774 if (FRC->getID() == Hexagon::IntRegsRegClassID) { 0
2775 bool T = genBitSplit(MI, RD, RC, AVB); 0
2776 T = T || simplifyExtractLow(MI, RD, RC, AVB); 0
2777 T = T || genExtractHalf(MI, RD, RC); 0
2778 T = T || genCombineHalf(MI, RD, RC); 0
2779 T = T || genExtractLow(MI, RD, RC); 0
2780 T = T || simplifyRCmp0(MI, RD); 0
2781 Changed |= T; 0
2782 continue; 0
2783 } 0
2784 ----
2785 if (FRC->getID() == Hexagon::PredRegsRegClassID) { 0
2786 bool T = simplifyTstbit(MI, RD, RC); 0
2787 Changed |= T; 0
2788 continue; 0
2789 } 0
2790 } ----
2791 return Changed; 0
2792 } 0
2793 ----
2794 bool HexagonBitSimplify::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
2795 if (skipFunction(MF.getFunction())) 0
2796 return false; 0
2797 ----
2798 auto &HST = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
2799 auto &HRI = *HST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
2800 auto &HII = *HST.getInstrInfo(); 0
2801 ----
2802 MDT = &getAnalysis(); 0
2803 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
2804 bool Changed; ----
2805 ----
2806 Changed = DeadCodeElimination(MF, *MDT).run(); 0
2807 ----
2808 const HexagonEvaluator HE(HRI, MRI, HII, MF); 0
2809 BitTracker BT(HE, MF); 0
2810 LLVM_DEBUG(BT.trace(true)); 0
2811 BT.run(); 0
2812 ----
2813 MachineBasicBlock &Entry = MF.front(); 0
2814 ----
2815 RegisterSet AIG; // Available registers for IG. 0
2816 ConstGeneration ImmG(BT, HII, MRI); 0
2817 Changed |= visitBlock(Entry, ImmG, AIG); 0
2818 ----
2819 RegisterSet ARE; // Available registers for RIE. 0
2820 RedundantInstrElimination RIE(BT, HII, HRI, MRI); 0
2821 bool Ried = visitBlock(Entry, RIE, ARE); 0
2822 if (Ried) { 0
2823 Changed = true; 0
2824 BT.run(); 0
2825 } ----
2826 ----
2827 RegisterSet ACG; // Available registers for CG. 0
2828 CopyGeneration CopyG(BT, HII, HRI, MRI); 0
2829 Changed |= visitBlock(Entry, CopyG, ACG); 0
2830 ----
2831 RegisterSet ACP; // Available registers for CP. 0
2832 CopyPropagation CopyP(HRI, MRI); 0
2833 Changed |= visitBlock(Entry, CopyP, ACP); 0
2834 ----
2835 Changed = DeadCodeElimination(MF, *MDT).run() || Changed; 0
2836 ----
2837 BT.run(); 0
2838 RegisterSet ABS; // Available registers for BS. 0
2839 BitSimplification BitS(BT, *MDT, HII, HRI, MRI, MF); 0
2840 Changed |= visitBlock(Entry, BitS, ABS); 0
2841 ----
2842 Changed = DeadCodeElimination(MF, *MDT).run() || Changed; 0
2843 ----
2844 if (Changed) { 0
2845 for (auto &B : MF) 0
2846 for (auto &I : B) 0
2847 I.clearKillInfo(); 0
2848 DeadCodeElimination(MF, *MDT).run(); 0
2849 } ----
2850 return Changed; 0
2851 } 0
2852 ----
2853 // Recognize loops where the code at the end of the loop matches the code ----
2854 // before the entry of the loop, and the matching code is such that is can ----
2855 // be simplified. This pass relies on the bit simplification above and only ----
2856 // prepares code in a way that can be handled by the bit simplifcation. ----
2857 // ----
2858 // This is the motivating testcase (and explanation): ----
2859 // ----
2860 // { ----
2861 // loop0(.LBB0_2, r1) // %for.body.preheader ----
2862 // r5:4 = memd(r0++#8) ----
2863 // } ----
2864 // { ----
2865 // r3 = lsr(r4, #16) ----
2866 // r7:6 = combine(r5, r5) ----
2867 // } ----
2868 // { ----
2869 // r3 = insert(r5, #16, #16) ----
2870 // r7:6 = vlsrw(r7:6, #16) ----
2871 // } ----
2872 // .LBB0_2: ----
2873 // { ----
2874 // memh(r2+#4) = r5 ----
2875 // memh(r2+#6) = r6 # R6 is really R5.H ----
2876 // } ----
2877 // { ----
2878 // r2 = add(r2, #8) ----
2879 // memh(r2+#0) = r4 ----
2880 // memh(r2+#2) = r3 # R3 is really R4.H ----
2881 // } ----
2882 // { ----
2883 // r5:4 = memd(r0++#8) ----
2884 // } ----
2885 // { # "Shuffling" code that sets up R3 and R6 ----
2886 // r3 = lsr(r4, #16) # so that their halves can be stored in the ----
2887 // r7:6 = combine(r5, r5) # next iteration. This could be folded into ----
2888 // } # the stores if the code was at the beginning ----
2889 // { # of the loop iteration. Since the same code ----
2890 // r3 = insert(r5, #16, #16) # precedes the loop, it can actually be moved ----
2891 // r7:6 = vlsrw(r7:6, #16) # there. ----
2892 // }:endloop0 ----
2893 // ----
2894 // ----
2895 // The outcome: ----
2896 // ----
2897 // { ----
2898 // loop0(.LBB0_2, r1) ----
2899 // r5:4 = memd(r0++#8) ----
2900 // } ----
2901 // .LBB0_2: ----
2902 // { ----
2903 // memh(r2+#4) = r5 ----
2904 // memh(r2+#6) = r5.h ----
2905 // } ----
2906 // { ----
2907 // r2 = add(r2, #8) ----
2908 // memh(r2+#0) = r4 ----
2909 // memh(r2+#2) = r4.h ----
2910 // } ----
2911 // { ----
2912 // r5:4 = memd(r0++#8) ----
2913 // }:endloop0 ----
2914 ----

2985 if (OpB.getMBB() == &B) { 0

2987 continue; 0

2990 PR = P.getOperand(i); 0

3002 bool HexagonLoopRescheduling::isConst(unsigned Reg) const { 0
3003 if (!BTP->has(Reg)) 0
3004 return false; 0
3005 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &RC = BTP->lookup(Reg); 0
3006 for (unsigned i = 0, w = RC.width(); i < w; ++i) { 0
3007 const BitTracker::BitValue &V = RC[i]; 0
3008 if (!V.is(0) && !V.is(1)) 0
3009 return false; 0
3010 } ----
3011 return true; 0
3012 } ----
3013 ----
3014 bool HexagonLoopRescheduling::isBitShuffle(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
3015 unsigned DefR) const { ----
3016 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
3017 switch (Opc) { 0
3018 case TargetOpcode::COPY: 0
3019 case Hexagon::S2_lsr_i_r: ----
3020 case Hexagon::S2_asr_i_r: ----
3021 case Hexagon::S2_asl_i_r: ----
3022 case Hexagon::S2_lsr_i_p: ----
3023 case Hexagon::S2_asr_i_p: ----
3024 case Hexagon::S2_asl_i_p: ----
3025 case Hexagon::S2_insert: ----
3026 case Hexagon::A2_or: ----
3027 case Hexagon::A2_orp: ----
3028 case Hexagon::A2_and: ----
3029 case Hexagon::A2_andp: ----
3030 case Hexagon::A2_combinew: ----
3031 case Hexagon::A4_combineri: ----
3032 case Hexagon::A4_combineir: ----
3033 case Hexagon::A2_combineii: ----
3034 case Hexagon::A4_combineii: ----
3035 case Hexagon::A2_combine_ll: ----
3036 case Hexagon::A2_combine_lh: ----
3037 case Hexagon::A2_combine_hl: ----
3038 case Hexagon::A2_combine_hh: ----
3039 return true; 0
3040 } ----
3041 return false; 0
3042 } ----
3043 ----
3044 bool HexagonLoopRescheduling::isStoreInput(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
3045 unsigned InpR) const { ----
3046 for (unsigned i = 0, n = MI->getNumOperands(); i < n; ++i) { 0
3047 const MachineOperand &Op = MI->getOperand(i); 0
3048 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
3049 continue; 0
3050 if (Op.getReg() == InpR) 0
3051 return i == n-1; 0
3052 } ----
3053 return false; 0
3054 } ----
3055 ----
3056 bool HexagonLoopRescheduling::isShuffleOf(unsigned OutR, unsigned InpR) const { 0
3057 if (!BTP->has(OutR) || !BTP->has(InpR)) 0
3058 return false; 0
3059 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &OutC = BTP->lookup(OutR); 0
3060 for (unsigned i = 0, w = OutC.width(); i < w; ++i) { 0
3061 const BitTracker::BitValue &V = OutC[i]; 0
3062 if (V.Type != BitTracker::BitValue::Ref) 0
3063 continue; 0
3064 if (V.RefI.Reg != InpR) 0
3065 return false; 0
3066 } ----
3067 return true; 0
3068 } ----
3069 ----
3070 bool HexagonLoopRescheduling::isSameShuffle(unsigned OutR1, unsigned InpR1, 0
3071 unsigned OutR2, unsigned &InpR2) const { ----
3072 if (!BTP->has(OutR1) || !BTP->has(InpR1) || !BTP->has(OutR2)) 0
3073 return false; 0
3074 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &OutC1 = BTP->lookup(OutR1); 0
3075 const BitTracker::RegisterCell &OutC2 = BTP->lookup(OutR2); 0
3076 unsigned W = OutC1.width(); 0
3077 unsigned MatchR = 0; 0
3078 if (W != OutC2.width()) 0
3079 return false; 0
3080 for (unsigned i = 0; i < W; ++i) { 0
3081 const BitTracker::BitValue &V1 = OutC1[i], &V2 = OutC2[i]; 0
3082 if (V1.Type != V2.Type || V1.Type == BitTracker::BitValue::One) 0
3083 return false; 0
3084 if (V1.Type != BitTracker::BitValue::Ref) 0
3085 continue; 0
3086 if (V1.RefI.Pos != V2.RefI.Pos) 0
3087 return false; 0
3088 if (V1.RefI.Reg != InpR1) 0
3089 return false; 0
3090 if (V2.RefI.Reg == 0 || V2.RefI.Reg == OutR2) 0
3091 return false; 0
3092 if (!MatchR) 0
3093 MatchR = V2.RefI.Reg; 0
3094 else if (V2.RefI.Reg != MatchR) 0
3095 return false; 0
3096 } ----
3097 InpR2 = MatchR; 0
3098 return true; 0
3099 } ----
3100 ----
3101 void HexagonLoopRescheduling::moveGroup(InstrGroup &G, MachineBasicBlock &LB, 0
3102 MachineBasicBlock &PB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator At, unsigned OldPhiR, ----
3103 unsigned NewPredR) { ----
3104 DenseMap RegMap; 0
3105 ----
3106 const TargetRegisterClass *PhiRC = MRI->getRegClass(NewPredR); 0
3107 Register PhiR = MRI->createVirtualRegister(PhiRC); 0
3108 BuildMI(LB, At, At->getDebugLoc(), HII->get(TargetOpcode::PHI), PhiR) 0
3109 .addReg(NewPredR) 0
3110 .addMBB(&PB) 0
3111 .addReg(G.Inp.Reg) 0
3112 .addMBB(&LB); 0
3113 RegMap.insert(std::make_pair(G.Inp.Reg, PhiR)); 0
3114 ----
3115 for (const MachineInstr *SI : llvm::reverse(G.Ins)) { 0
3116 unsigned DR = getDefReg(SI); 0
3117 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(DR); 0
3118 Register NewDR = MRI->createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3119 DebugLoc DL = SI->getDebugLoc(); 0
3120 ----
3121 auto MIB = BuildMI(LB, At, DL, HII->get(SI->getOpcode()), NewDR); 0
3122 for (const MachineOperand &Op : SI->operands()) { 0
3123 if (!Op.isReg()) { 0
3124 MIB.add(Op); 0
3125 continue; 0
3126 } ----
3127 if (!Op.isUse()) 0
3128 continue; 0
3129 unsigned UseR = RegMap[Op.getReg()]; 0
3130 MIB.addReg(UseR, 0, Op.getSubReg()); 0
3131 } ----
3132 RegMap.insert(std::make_pair(DR, NewDR)); 0
3133 } 0
3134 ----
3135 HBS::replaceReg(OldPhiR, RegMap[G.Out.Reg], *MRI); 0
3136 } 0
3137 ----
3138 bool HexagonLoopRescheduling::processLoop(LoopCand &C) { 0
3139 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Processing loop in " << printMBBReference(*C.LB) 0
3140 << "\n"); ----
3141 std::vector Phis; 0
3142 for (auto &I : *C.LB) { 0
3143 if (!I.isPHI()) 0
3144 break; 0
3145 unsigned PR = getDefReg(&I); 0
3146 if (isConst(PR)) 0
3147 continue; 0
3148 bool BadUse = false, GoodUse = false; 0
3149 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MRI->use_operands(PR)) { 0
3150 const MachineInstr *UseI = MO.getParent(); 0
3151 if (UseI->getParent() != C.LB) { 0
3152 BadUse = true; 0
3153 break; 0
3154 } ----
3155 if (isBitShuffle(UseI, PR) || isStoreInput(UseI, PR)) 0
3156 GoodUse = true; 0
3157 } ----
3158 if (BadUse || !GoodUse) 0
3159 continue; 0
3160 ----
3161 Phis.push_back(PhiInfo(I, *C.LB)); 0
3162 } ----
3163 ----
3164 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
3165 dbgs() << "Phis: {"; ----
3166 for (auto &I : Phis) { ----
3167 dbgs() << ' ' << printReg(I.DefR, HRI) << "=phi(" ----
3168 << printReg(I.PR.Reg, HRI, I.PR.Sub) << ":b" << I.PB->getNumber() ----
3169 << ',' << printReg(I.LR.Reg, HRI, I.LR.Sub) << ":b" ----
3170 << I.LB->getNumber() << ')'; ----
3171 } ----
3172 dbgs() << " }\n"; ----
3173 }); ----
3174 ----
3175 if (Phis.empty()) 0
3176 return false; 0
3177 ----
3178 bool Changed = false; 0
3179 InstrList ShufIns; 0
3180 ----
3181 // Go backwards in the block: for each bit shuffling instruction, check ----
3182 // if that instruction could potentially be moved to the front of the loop: ----
3183 // the output of the loop cannot be used in a non-shuffling instruction ----
3184 // in this loop. ----
3185 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::reverse(*C.LB)) { 0
3186 if (MI.isTerminator()) 0
3187 continue; 0
3188 if (MI.isPHI()) 0
3189 break; 0
3190 ----
3191 RegisterSet Defs; 0
3192 HBS::getInstrDefs(MI, Defs); 0
3193 if (Defs.count() != 1) 0
3194 continue; 0
3195 Register DefR = Defs.find_first(); 0
3196 if (!DefR.isVirtual()) 0
3197 continue; 0
3198 if (!isBitShuffle(&MI, DefR)) 0
3199 continue; 0
3200 ----
3201 bool BadUse = false; 0
3202 for (auto UI = MRI->use_begin(DefR), UE = MRI->use_end(); UI != UE; ++UI) { 0
3203 MachineInstr *UseI = UI->getParent(); 0
3204 if (UseI->getParent() == C.LB) { 0
3205 if (UseI->isPHI()) { 0
3206 // If the use is in a phi node in this loop, then it should be ----
3207 // the value corresponding to the back edge. ----
3208 unsigned Idx = UI.getOperandNo(); 0
3209 if (UseI->getOperand(Idx+1).getMBB() != C.LB) 0
3210 BadUse = true; 0
3211 } else { ----
3212 if (!llvm::is_contained(ShufIns, UseI)) 0
3213 BadUse = true; 0
3214 } ----
3215 } else { ----
3216 // There is a use outside of the loop, but there is no epilog block ----
3217 // suitable for a copy-out. ----
3218 if (C.EB == nullptr) 0
3219 BadUse = true; 0
3220 } ----
3221 if (BadUse) 0
3222 break; 0
3223 } ----
3224 ----
3225 if (BadUse) 0
3226 continue; 0
3227 ShufIns.push_back(&MI); 0
3228 } 0
3229 ----
3230 // Partition the list of shuffling instructions into instruction groups, ----
3231 // where each group has to be moved as a whole (i.e. a group is a chain of ----
3232 // dependent instructions). A group produces a single live output register, ----
3233 // which is meant to be the input of the loop phi node (although this is ----
3234 // not checked here yet). It also uses a single register as its input, ----
3235 // which is some value produced in the loop body. After moving the group ----
3236 // to the beginning of the loop, that input register would need to be ----
3237 // the loop-carried register (through a phi node) instead of the (currently ----
3238 // loop-carried) output register. ----
3239 using InstrGroupList = std::vector; ----
3240 InstrGroupList Groups; 0
3241 ----
3242 for (unsigned i = 0, n = ShufIns.size(); i < n; ++i) { 0
3243 MachineInstr *SI = ShufIns[i]; 0
3244 if (SI == nullptr) 0
3245 continue; 0
3246 ----
3247 InstrGroup G; 0
3248 G.Ins.push_back(SI); 0
3249 G.Out.Reg = getDefReg(SI); 0
3250 RegisterSet Inputs; 0
3251 HBS::getInstrUses(*SI, Inputs); 0
3252 ----
3253 for (unsigned j = i+1; j < n; ++j) { 0
3254 MachineInstr *MI = ShufIns[j]; 0
3255 if (MI == nullptr) 0
3256 continue; 0
3257 RegisterSet Defs; 0
3258 HBS::getInstrDefs(*MI, Defs); 0
3259 // If this instruction does not define any pending inputs, skip it. ----
3260 if (!Defs.intersects(Inputs)) 0
3261 continue; 0
3262 // Otherwise, add it to the current group and remove the inputs that ----
3263 // are defined by MI. ----
3264 G.Ins.push_back(MI); 0
3265 Inputs.remove(Defs); 0
3266 // Then add all registers used by MI. ----
3267 HBS::getInstrUses(*MI, Inputs); 0
3268 ShufIns[j] = nullptr; 0
3269 } 0
3270 ----
3271 // Only add a group if it requires at most one register. ----
3272 if (Inputs.count() > 1) 0
3273 continue; 0
3274 auto LoopInpEq = [G] (const PhiInfo &P) -> bool { 0
3275 return G.Out.Reg == P.LR.Reg; 0
3276 }; 0
3277 if (llvm::none_of(Phis, LoopInpEq)) 0
3278 continue; 0
3279 ----
3280 G.Inp.Reg = Inputs.find_first(); 0
3281 Groups.push_back(G); 0
3282 } 0
3283 ----
3284 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
3285 for (unsigned i = 0, n = Groups.size(); i < n; ++i) { ----
3286 InstrGroup &G = Groups[i]; ----
3287 dbgs() << "Group[" << i << "] inp: " ----
3288 << printReg(G.Inp.Reg, HRI, G.Inp.Sub) ----
3289 << " out: " << printReg(G.Out.Reg, HRI, G.Out.Sub) << "\n"; ----
3290 for (const MachineInstr *MI : G.Ins) ----
3291 dbgs() << " " << MI; ----
3292 } ----
3293 }); ----
3294 ----
3295 for (InstrGroup &G : Groups) { 0
3296 if (!isShuffleOf(G.Out.Reg, G.Inp.Reg)) 0
3297 continue; 0
3298 auto LoopInpEq = [G] (const PhiInfo &P) -> bool { 0
3299 return G.Out.Reg == P.LR.Reg; 0
3300 }; 0
3301 auto F = llvm::find_if(Phis, LoopInpEq); 0
3302 if (F == Phis.end()) 0
3303 continue; 0
3304 unsigned PrehR = 0; 0
3305 if (!isSameShuffle(G.Out.Reg, G.Inp.Reg, F->PR.Reg, PrehR)) { 0
3306 const MachineInstr *DefPrehR = MRI->getVRegDef(F->PR.Reg); 0
3307 unsigned Opc = DefPrehR->getOpcode(); 0
3308 if (Opc != Hexagon::A2_tfrsi && Opc != Hexagon::A2_tfrpi) 0
3309 continue; 0
3310 if (!DefPrehR->getOperand(1).isImm()) 0
3311 continue; 0
3312 if (DefPrehR->getOperand(1).getImm() != 0) 0
3313 continue; 0
3314 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(G.Inp.Reg); 0
3315 if (RC != MRI->getRegClass(F->PR.Reg)) { 0
3316 PrehR = MRI->createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
3317 unsigned TfrI = (RC == &Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass) ? Hexagon::A2_tfrsi 0
3318 : Hexagon::A2_tfrpi; ----
3319 auto T = C.PB->getFirstTerminator(); 0
3320 DebugLoc DL = (T != C.PB->end()) ? T->getDebugLoc() : DebugLoc(); 0
3321 BuildMI(*C.PB, T, DL, HII->get(TfrI), PrehR) 0
3322 .addImm(0); 0
3323 } else { 0
3324 PrehR = F->PR.Reg; 0
3325 } ----
3326 } ----
3327 // isSameShuffle could match with PrehR being of a wider class than ----
3328 // G.Inp.Reg, for example if G shuffles the low 32 bits of its input, ----
3329 // it would match for the input being a 32-bit register, and PrehR ----
3330 // being a 64-bit register (where the low 32 bits match). This could ----
3331 // be handled, but for now skip these cases. ----
3332 if (MRI->getRegClass(PrehR) != MRI->getRegClass(G.Inp.Reg)) 0
3333 continue; 0
3334 moveGroup(G, *F->LB, *F->PB, F->LB->getFirstNonPHI(), F->DefR, PrehR); 0
3335 Changed = true; 0
3336 } 0
3337 ----
3338 return Changed; 0
3339 } 0
3340 ----
3341 bool HexagonLoopRescheduling::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
3342 if (skipFunction(MF.getFunction())) 0
3343 return false; 0
3344 ----
3345 auto &HST = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
3346 HII = HST.getInstrInfo(); 0
3347 HRI = HST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
3348 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
3349 const HexagonEvaluator HE(*HRI, *MRI, *HII, MF); 0
3350 BitTracker BT(HE, MF); 0
3351 LLVM_DEBUG(BT.trace(true)); 0
3352 BT.run(); 0
3353 BTP = &BT; 0
3354 ----
3355 std::vector Cand; 0
3356 ----
3357 for (auto &B : MF) { 0
3358 if (B.pred_size() != 2 || B.succ_size() != 2) 0
3359 continue; 0
3360 MachineBasicBlock *PB = nullptr; 0
3361 bool IsLoop = false; 0
3362 for (MachineBasicBlock *Pred : B.predecessors()) { 0
3363 if (Pred != &B) 0
3364 PB = Pred; 0
3365 else ----
3366 IsLoop = true; 0
3367 } ----
3368 if (!IsLoop) 0
3369 continue; 0
3370 ----
3371 MachineBasicBlock *EB = nullptr; 0
3372 for (MachineBasicBlock *Succ : B.successors()) { 0
3373 if (Succ == &B) 0
3374 continue; 0
3375 // Set EP to the epilog block, if it has only 1 predecessor (i.e. the ----
3376 // edge from B to EP is non-critical. ----
3377 if (Succ->pred_size() == 1) 0
3378 EB = Succ; 0
3379 break; 0
3380 } ----
3381 ----
3382 Cand.push_back(LoopCand(&B, PB, EB)); 0
3383 } ----
3384 ----
3385 bool Changed = false; 0
3386 for (auto &C : Cand) 0
3387 Changed |= processLoop(C); 0
3388 ----
3389 return Changed; 0
3390 } 0
3391 ----
